column13: Best bang for your buck! Works like a charm!
column14:
This Professional Blackhead and Acne Remover Kit is made of surgical stainless steel; which means it is built to last. This kit contains 5 different double sided extractors all targeted on specifically removing different sized and hard-to-reach impurities such as blemishes, blackheads, whiteheads, and pimples. The kit also comes with a plastic pouch for easy storage. The extractors are easy to use and the textured handles provide an anti-slip grip, comfort and precision when extracting whiteheads, blackheads or blemishes. I rarely have acne, whitehead or blackheads, but when they pop up I like to take action in removing them asap!

I have a tool similar to these, but I really like the fact that the kit comes with different tips. I especially like the needle point tip. Makes it really easy to remove the stubborn ones. After use I like to rub them down with a cotton ball that I soaked with rubbing alcohol.

I’m happy with the Blackhead and Acne Remover Kit. I would definitely recommend and would purchase it again.

column6: Nourish Beaute Vitamins Hair Loss Shampoo and Conditioner w/ Natural Growth Factors, Argan Oil & Biotin
column14:
So after much research on Amazon I decided to buy Nourish Vitamins hair growth support SHAMPOO......its been 3 and a half weeks that I am using this shampoo and I thought I would write my review today. My hair has been excessively falling for the past 1 year so I started my pursuit of addressing the issue of my hair loss and tried everything that anybody suggested....this is the ninth product/treatment that I started so you can well imagine how much research I must have done! Needless to say when everything else failed, with no optimism left, I started to use this shampoo and I was washing my hair with it every other day and to my utter astonishment I started to see less hair fall...so I also decided to start the Nourish hair growth support VITAMINS, as I wanted to treat my hair loss problem inside and out.
Well about 3 + weeks after I can surely say that I am seeing less and less hair fall, which is a big deal for me, as anyone who is loosing hair knows how much it hurts to see your hair on the comb and on the pillow case!! So this morning when I was combing my hair I only saw about 4-5 strands come out and that for me is a huge difference from before. I am very happy and relieved to find a product that is finally working out for me! These products have given me hope that I also can transform my falling, fine hair to healthy, strong hair!
I am also going to write another review in a month to tell you guys how my hair are doing and if I have seen any new growth as it is still early to comment on that.
I would highly recommend this combination of Nourish Shampoo and Vitamins to anyone who is loosing hair.....
Thank you Nourish!!

column6: Clearly Natural Glycerine Bar Soap, Unscented, 3 Count, 4 oz each
column13: Doesn't feel like I'm getting clean with this weak soap
column14: I've been disappointed with this soap. I received it as a gift. I had asked for bars of glycerine soap after having bought some fancier glycerine soap bars at a specialty soap store. I loved how those other bars cleaned well and moisturized my skin without harsh chemicals, but I couldn't afford to keep paying $6 or $7 per bar. I was excited to receive a six-pack of Clearly Natural unscented glycerin soap bars as a gift, thinking they'd be similar to what I previously had purchased for myself, but I'm finding that's not the case at all. Mostly, I'm frustrated by how little cleaning power these bars seem to have. They do not suds up, as other reviewers have commented, and some think that's a good thing, while others seem disappointed as I am. Even if suds aren't necessary for cleaning, as one reviewer claims, these bars don't seem to offer whatever else is necessary for sustained or economical cleaning either. When I rub them vigorously on my wash cloth, it still feels like almost no cleaning agent is on the cloth, and I end up rubbing a wet, not-soapy cloth on my body. The bar diminishes in size, but I don't feel as though I'm getting clean. I eventually moved a bar from my shower to the bathroom sink, on the theory that rubbing the bar directly on my hands will transfer more soap to the body rather than using a wash cloth as a cleaning medium. It seems this soap is better used as a sink bar than as a bath bar, but I'm still disappointed, because that's not what I was looking for.

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column14: So, I went into this knowing I had sensitive skin but willing to try something new as I have used similar products before. Man do I regret that. I think I  have chemical burns under my arms and the fragrance is haunting my nostrils. Within seconds of my first application my underarms started to burn, which I thought would pass...but it didn't. I ended up running into my bathroom to take a shower to remove the, as promised, already dry "fast drying" gel. That part they didn't lie about, I think this stuff dried in seconds and merged with the cells in my armpits! I ended up washing under my arms several times with soothing body wash until at least the immediate burn was gone. However, even after 3 washes I still reeked of the fragrance of this deodorant. While I am pretty sure I removed all of the actual product it seemed to have tattooed me with its smell, even lingering into the next day....which I guess was the one part of this product that really did "outlast" my expectations. I am not sure if it is just my sensitive skin that caused the painful reaction or if this product works by scarring your sweat glands so badly you cannot sweat anymore, but either way I am not into that sorta "beauty is pain" mentality so this is a giant NO for me. The fragrance however was nice, just really overpowering and didn't go away. No way could I have worn my own perfume with this without a major clashing of smells. Secret really needs to make their products gentler and pull back a little on the "french shower" methodology of odor control...smelling like perfume with an undertone of B.O is still smelling like B.O, so really no need for that level of fragrance! I did receive this item for free from Secret to review, but all opinions are my own honest opinions.

column14: I will never go back to using regular deodorant or antiperspirant again. This stuff is clear and will not show up on your clothes. Ever. column6: Shampoo for Oily Hair & Oily Scalp - Natural Dandruff Treatment for Women & Men - Hair Loss Products - Hair Strengthener - Itchy Scalp Treatment - Beautiful Hair Care - Clarifying Shampoo Sulfate Free
column13: Gets my hair squeaky clean, but there's still grease.
column14:
To give a little background on my hair first: ever since puberty hit, I've had very oily hair. I HAVE to wash my hair everyday. Within 24 hours, my hair is all oily and gross. I've tried maybe a few different kinds of shampoo in the hopes of fixing it, but they were all drying type of shampoos that think if you strip your hair of all oils that it goes away, and it just makes it worst.

Anyway, on to the review: I bought this shampoo around 2 weeks ago or so. It is summer here, in NC, and I also live near the coast, so the humidity is horrible. I sweat a lot, and when I wipe my face, it tends to get in my hair, which overtime gives the effect of greasy hair. That being said, I obviously haven't tried this shampoo out when I'm not sweating a lot, so that may have some effect on how it's working with my oil issues. It doesn't or hasn't so far, made me be able to go a second day without washing my hair. As I sit here and type this, my hair is all oily and gross, but I washed my hair at 5:30 am yesterday morning, and I did sweat a lot yesterday.

I will say, however that it does get your hair squeaky clean. You can hear it squeak in the shower. I have hair down to my elbows and you only need a quarter sized amount to wash your hair. You only need to wash your scalp, not the rest of your hair. Everytime I get in the shower and squirt the quarter sized amount in my hair, I always think "I need more." I just take a little on my finger tips and start massaging it on various parts of my hair. I scrub the back of my head towards my neck, cause it gets really itchy if I don't wash it everyday. This shampoo lathers so good.

I read another review on here about how a lady who had horrible cystic acne would use it as face wash as well. I've been doing that too, seeing as how I have an oily face too. It hasn't changed anything with that yet either, except that if I do have any acne come up, it heals it a lot faster.

I mainly got thisshampoo because it is silicone and sulfate free. I saw a girl on youtube talk about how silicone weighs your hair down and essentially creates frizz. I have frizzy curly hair, and wanted to see if it helped. I haven't been able to wear my hair down yet straight from the shower to see if it helps, but I can see a difference when I take my hair down in the mornings before I wash it.

I follow this shampoo with the Silk 18, and I will say this: the conditioner smells amazing. I tell my friends that it smells like the good vanilla, not the nasty car air freshener vanilla.

I'm thinking that maybe I just need to wait until fall/autumn is here, when I don't sweat as much, and I've really had the chance to see if it works like it's supposed to, maybe my sebaceous gland needs more repair than normal? I don't know. I will update in a few months or so and give you the low down on it then too.

column6: LumiEssence Organic Advanced Brightening Repair Treatment with Kojic Acid, Arbutin & Vitamin C
column13: Buy it, you're going to love the results!
column14:
I have used other dark spot corrector serums which have stung, or caused a tingling. Happily to report, this one does not bother my skin, and I've had no adverse reaction.

It leaves my skin feeling baby-skin soft, and smooth like vanilla ice cream. Additionally, it doesn't have a heavy, thick feel to it at all. I am very pleased with the results!

If you're unfamiliar with its primary ingredient, Kojic Acid, it is a remedy for the treatment of pigment problems, and age spots. Discovered in 1989, kojic acid works similarly to hydroquinone. Kojic acid is derived from a fungus, and studies have shown that it is effective as a lightening agent, slowing production of melanin (brown pigment).

column14:
I am writing to you because I ordered the neem oil from your company and want to tell you first hand how God sent this neem plant is. No wonder it's called "tree of life".

I have been using the oil on my nails. 1) for fungal infection, 2) for ridges and cracked nails. The ridges were so bad that there were black lines from the nail bed all the way to the top of the nail.

I work in my garden and do not wear gloves so my nails take a beating.

It has been 3 weeks I have been using the oil (100% pure) and what a difference. I wish I had taken pictures of my hand to send to you as proof. My nails look so beautiful and healthy. No fungus infection, no ridges, no cracks, and growing strong. My cuticles are also healthy, not red and peeling.

I have a neem tree in my garden and I use the leaves in various ways.

Thank you for the 100 % pure neem oil.

Zee Madhany

column6: Foxbrim Ocean Mineral Lotion & Face Moisturizer - Seaweed Bio-Complex, 100mL/3.4oz
column14: I think this is a great daily moisturizer for many skin types. My skin gets progressively more oily over the course of the day and certain products will speed that up, but that is not the case here. This Ocean Mineral Lotion sinks in fast while still being hydrating. It's nice not to have a greasy, tacky layer of moisturizer on your skin before you do your makeup! I really like that it contains aloe, which helps my redness, and jojoba oil, which matches my skin's sebum, which makes for less breakouts and less flakey dry skin! I also like that it contains ocean minerals, as the dead sea mud soaps and masks really helped with my acne and my skin responds quite favorably. It also has hyaluronic acid in it as well, so make sure to apply over a toner(no alcohol!) for maximum benefits.  I also like that it was made here in the US, and their products are not tested on animals. I also like that this came in an airless pump instead of a tub, it shows Foxbrim really pays attention to the products they are making!

column6: Suave For Men Hair and Body Wash, (Pack of 6)
column13: Great For The Budget Minded Minimalist
column14:
Suave is know to have 3-in-1 hair/body/shave combos. Here is a two in one that could probably also be considered a conditioner, if a light one.

I'm I guy and I still have a collection of shampoos, conditioners, body washes and soaps in the shower. Usually to just use whatever I'm in the mood for, or grab something specific to address a certain hygiene topic that I feel needs some attention. Suave Men's Body Wash, Hair & Body 2 in 1 takes the fun of the choice out of that, but also all of the guess work. It is a better body wash than shampoo/conditioner combo, but it does the job. It cleans and rinses off easily, and leaves a light manly scent that fades in about an hour. If you want to get feng shui and remove the clutter from your shower, this is really all the product many men should need. It isn't organic and all-natural, but if you don't mind that, it can't be beat for the price.

~ Kort

column6: Majestic Pure Essential Oil, 100% Pure and Natural with Therapeutic Grade, Premium Quality Oil 4fl
column13: The scent of lemon and the power of a pure oil
column14:
I am big into aromatherapy, so I work with a variety of oils. Lemon oil is one of my favorites, though. It, and it blended with other oils, gives a wonderful fresh fragrance that fills the room with a clean, crisp scent. Its great for energizing and refreshing after a long day. This particular brand is very pure. I only need two drops in my warmer to fill my entire living room.

The other reason I like this oil so much is because it's a multi-tasker. I can do so much more that fragrance with this, so it's a very good thing that it comes in such a large bottle! It's a big component in my homemade cleaning sprays and polishes. Being so concentrated, a little goes a long way. There are hundreds of formulas online that you can use to make all kinds of cleaning products at home that involve lemon oil, and this is one of the best brands I have found for pure OILS. If you're new to essential oils and how much they can do for you, the company will give you an introduction with purchase, but I would suggest googling "Lemon oil<uses<household" for a ton of uses and ideas that can save you money and unnecessary chemicals every day.

column6: Retinol Cream - Best Moisturizing Night Cream - Anti Aging Cream with Retinol , Vitamin C and Hyaluronic Acid to Draw Moisture From the Environment to the Skin for a Superb Moisturizing Effect - Also with Aloe Vera , Vitamin E ,Shea Butter. Antiaging Cream for Face , Neck and Eyes - Use Night and Day .Restore and Renew Firmness, Elasticity and Thickness to the Skin. Top Quality Anti Wrinkle Serum
column13: A night cream that really does work.
column14:
Wonderful is all I can say. I have used night creams from cheap to very high end, some are a good hit, some aren't worth dragging home and the price of them doesn't seem to have a bearing on how good they are in my opinion. I was given a chance to try this on a promotion and I am glad I did. I seen it was a 2 ounce bottle, (when most are 1 ounce or 1.7 ounce), looked at the price and figured it would be average. I was wrong! It is packaged in an airless pump bottle, solid white to prevent any oxidation or chemical changes. Now remember I am 55 and I have not taken the best care of my hands I should have, I do dishes, clean etc all without gloves, I hate gloves! Anyway out of the box I put about a half pump on the back of my hand, rubbed it in, absorbed very quickly, left no sticky or oily residue, felt really good. I set here reading ingredients, took a pic of the ingredient list on bottle I will attach to review, (the ingredient list is very long and all wonderful ingredients so I knew someone would want to see a list). I looked down and noticed the back of my left hand, was smoother than the right, the little age lines are nice and plumped out. Wow, was my first thought. I have used it now for 4 nights and I can see a fairly big difference in the lines and crows feet I had started to the outside corners and under my eyes. Also lines around mouth are gone, (didn't have very bad ones around mouth anyway, just starting but they are gone). The cream smells wonderful, very light light rose, goes away quickly, but smells clean and good. It is a thicker cream but it just melts when you massage it in. I am truly loving this stuff! My skin is brighter, looks healthy, firmer, lines are lessened. This product will remain at the top of my list, as I feel with continued usage the difference in my skin will continue to improve.

column13: I love this line of products!
column14:
I started using this line of products a few months ago after reading several positive reviews. I'm 36 have always battled severe acne and discoloration. It's generally horrible. I started with just the serum, then added the cleanser, then the night cream, then the toner and then the mask.

Overall, this combination of products has drastically improved the look feel and overall health of my skin. The cleanser specifically is very gentle on my skin and I feel it does a great job removing dirt and oil and my skin doesn't feel dried out after I finish washing.

I now can wear less makeup and even feel comfortable wearing my hair out of my face on a regular basis. I've never felt better about my own face and it's because I decided to invest in a line of quality products that actually works for me. I have tried several other product lines on both the mainstream cosmetic side and the natural side resulting in poor or nightmarish results.

There's something about this line that just works for me and
I'm so thankful. I may sound a little dramatic here but for me it's a big deal. Being able to actually like the skin on my face has been a big life changer for me. I recommend this line to anyone with combination and sensitive skin. It all takes a little getting used to but it's completely worth it.

column6: Puracy Natural Liquid Hand Soap
column13: Great NATURAL hand soap, very pleasant smell.
column14:
This 100% natural liquid hand soap by Puracy is a great all natural soap.

It contains no phosphates, chlorine, ammonia, or dyes of any kind. Instead, it uses plant and sugar based ingredients which surprisingly are very effective at cleaning your hands without harming your skin. It cuts through grease and grime very well and is comparable to some of the top brands that aren't as gentle on your skin.

Its an interesting decision on Puracy's part when it comes to the fragrance, typically lavender is used for soothing/calming in lotions but they decided to throw a little bit into some hand soap. At first I wasn't sold on the idea but I have a habit of washing my hands as soon as I come home from work (I don't get home until 9-930pm) and I have come to enjoy the scent very much. I am a huge lavender fan, I use lavender oil nightly in my diffuser which is bed side so this made perfect sense once I really thought about it.

You are paying a premium for Puracy's product line, there is no doubt about that however it really is quality product. This is more of a "Whole Foods" type product not something you'd typically find at Walmart or stores like that. You do get what you pay for when it comes to the Puracy line.

I received a sample for review purposes.

column6: Vitamin C Serum 20 for Face with Hyaluronic Acid & Vitamin E Oil, that Helps Fade Age Spots, Clear Adult Acne & Get Rid of Wrinkles for a Glowing & Younger Looking Skin
column13: Probably a great product, but it’s just wasn’t for me
column14:
I was given the opportunity to purchase this Vitamin C Serum at a very deep discount for testing purposes. That does not affect my opinion in any way. My review is my own and completely honest.

Honestly – this may not have been the past purchase for me. I recently turned 30 and do not suffer from fine lines or wrinkles. Well maybe I do, but I just don’t care enough about them to be concerned and need a product to correct them. I used this serum for a few weeks and did not notice any significant changes in my facial skin. That isn’t a negative thing – there is just nothing that I noticed which had changed. So I am neutral as to the visual effects of this product.

As for the texture and consistency of the product – it was a really a great product. It was not too oily and it had a really good consistency. It did not dry out my skin at all. I have very sensitive skin, especially on my face, so I am always nervous about trying new products. This serum was a good for my skin and did not cause any irritation.

Again, this product just wasn’t for me at this time in my life. It’s a great product, but just not for me.

column6: Clairol Balsam Hair Color 12 Natural Black 1 Kit
column14:
I have been coloring my hair for years. I have naturally dark blonde hair. I use Natural Instincts to get rid of my gray every 2 months or so. Normally I stick to the blonde or light brown colors. They fade really quickly though. From sun and the pool my hair was lighter than normal but I wanted to change it up, so I tried Cinnaberry, a auburn shade. I probably should not have tried it on the blondish hair. At first it was a bright reddish, pink color. And...there wasn't really enough in the bottle to cover all my hair. My hair is a little pass shoulder length and is a medium thickness, so one bottle should be plenty. It was patchy in areas.

Luckily, red doesn't hold well in my hair and after 3 washes and swimming in the pool, it is now a normal looking red color, though still splotchy. I'd recommend this for brunettes and if you have longer than shoulder length hair, get two boxes. One thing I love about Natural Instincts is that it does wash out and it doesn't dry out your hair.

So, I tried something new and it didn't work out so well for me. I'll stick to my blonde and light brown shades from now on.

column6: Alpha Hydrox 14% AHA Serum
column14: I love this product. I've been using a 10% glycolic cream by a different brand for about a year. I like it but it don't creams. I'm more of a serum girl and this is perfect. In the morning, I wash with African black soap and apply 10% benzoyl peroxide cream. It's not overly creamy like lotion and it absorbs fast. At night I wash my face with the same soap and apply the AHA serum. It's all I need. I use it on my chest and neck too. Once a week, I'll use a PMD and I don't use the serum afterwards because it'll burn and I've done that before. Follow the directions. Especially if you're sensitive. I only use 4 drops of the serum. Just 4 and that's it. I put the drops in palm and use my fingertips to spread on my face. It's a little watery but that's fine. It dries quick. I will repurchase this again. Definitely recommend. column13: Fractionated -v- Virgin?  Depends on what it will be used for:)
column14:
Fractionated coconut oil is a fraction of the whole oil: Certain components of the oil are separated or removed from the oil for a particular use. Different uses of fractionated coconut oil include industrial, medical applications and beauty products. However, it is not the complete, virgin coconut oil.

Virgin coconut oil retains the plant’s original chemical composition – and consequently the plant’s therapeutic benefits. Coconut oil contains for the most part saturated fatty acids, with a small percentage of monounsaturated fatty acids and polyunsaturated fatty acids. It also contains glycerides. Natural coconut oil contains short and medium-chain length triglycerides whereas fractionated coconut oil may have certain medium-chain fatty acids removed or separated.

USES OF FRACTIONATED COCONUT OIL:

Being thin and stable, it has plenty of uses which can be broadly categorized in the following applications.

*Cosmetics - It is widely used in the preparation of soaps, lotions, ointments and other cosmetics.

*Aromatherapy - It is used as a carrier oil, since it facilitates the absorption of other oils and herbal extracts.

*Medicines - -It is used due to its antiseptic and disinfectant properties.

*Hair Care - It is also used in a number of hair care applications.

*Culinary Usage - It is used in cooking, as it does not go rancid easily and is very stable.

#1: My personal preference for this oil is in my hair care regime. I use coconut oil (virgin) in a deep conditioning treatment once per week. I coat my entire head of hair, from root to tip and leave it on overnight. Now, I normally have to wear a silk scarf or use an old designated pillow case, otherwise...well you can imagine. I've been doing this for years, however, I was offered this fractionated coconut oil in lieu of a fair review, so I wanted to try it out and I'm really happy that I did.

I really like the options of bottom tops, and chose the pump dispenser and this makes it really easy to use. I've don't two treatments on my hair and my hair seems to completely absorb this oil much better than virgin coconut oil. I've been really pleased with how soft my hair has been after the wash. Of course, it's not as heavy as virgin coconut oil either.

I also like to calm static or frizzies from my hair with a dab of this and comb through my hair. It tames it and leaves a nice sheen without the greasiness.

#2: I have used this as a carrier oil with cinnamon essential oil, which can be really strong. I like to use cinnamon oil on flaky, dry skin patches and it smells good as well. I've been happy with this application as it absorbs quickly and I don't feel greasy like when I normally use grape seed oil. It is also nice straight on the skin, again, it absorbs quickly and is not greasy.

#3: I have sautéed onions, ginger, garlic, and tomatoes - garam masala + cumin + curry = base for Indian curry or korma. column13: Do NOT buy if you want a close shave!
column14: I bought this as a replacement for my previous Braun shaver, as has been my practice for many years.  I've simply bought the best Braun available and been very happy, until now. The problem is that this would be perceived as "the best" based on price, which is apparently no longer true.  I have been using this razor for 4 months, have charged, cleaned, and done everything in between, and can now say IT SIMPLY IS INFERIOR TO PREVIOUS MODELS. Here's why:  it has 3 power settings, with the dark blue labeled as the strongest, but that is a mislabeling, as the settings should be "weak," "weaker," and "weakest!"  Both of my older Brauns (which are almost worn out) shave my beard WAY closer than this thing!  Buyer beware, as sometimes you don't get what you paid for, despite a steep cost!  I'm unfortunately in the market for a new electric razor.

column14: I saw the travel size sold as a set with regular Waterpik at store. So, here's my opinion:  The Flosser for Kids are cheaper than the adult's Travel size.  The Flosser for Kids hold enough water for one use, and the water reservoir fits upside down for packing.  The dials are different:  The regular adult size (for home use) has a dial from 1 to 10.  I like to use the adult one at home around 7 or 8, sometimes 9 (I have braces right now.)  The Floosser for Kids only have 3 lines on the dial, but the second one or some where between the second and the 3rd line was about the same as around 8 in the Adults.  I'm happy to be able to take the Flosser for Kids on the road, and not have to miss the one at home.

((((CRI). This is the accuracy of the ability of the bulbs light to show colors in their true color.
> 100 being the highest number, = for a black body (incandescent lamps are effectively black-bodies)
> 80 plus for typical LED. (some manufacturers say their LEDs are up to 98 CRI)
> 50 for basic fluorescent lights, to 90 for the best tr-phosphor type)))
So given this scale = this 80 CRI - fluorescent is pretty true to life color.

The mirror rotates easily - it's glare & fog free.
The 10,000 hour bulb at an hour a day is expected to last over 27 years.
This 'FSL' = full spectrum light is engineered to simulate natural daylight indoors, for reducing eye strain & glare.

I have only one con = one mirror had several specks that appeared to be manufacture defects,
but lighter fluid on a cloth removed them all but two. There very small (a pin prick) & not an issue for me but may be for some.

column6: ARM & HAMMER Whitening Booster 2.50 oz
column13: Works with consistent use, and a must have for coffee drinkers!
column14:
I was really skeptical of this stuff at first since I rarely have success with DIY whitening, but I'm happy to announce that it truly does work. It's NOT toothpaste but a booster meant to be used with your regular toothpaste. Just add a small amount of this to your toothbrush along with your usual toothpaste and brush as normal.

The key to this stuff is consistent use. I do think it started making a very subtle difference right away, but it was at least a week or two of consistent (2X a day) use before I started to notice a real difference. I've now been using it (off and on) for over a year and while I may have reached my set point as far as how white my teeth will get without professional whitening, I'm very happy with results I've gotten from this and will continue to use it since it definitely helps keep new stains at bay. I doubt it will do much for deep discoloration (esp. stains due to things like decay), but it works great for mild to moderate staining from things like coffee.

I usually worry about whitening products because I know they can cause enamel deterioration and the like, but I haven't experienced any increased sensitivity or deterioration that I can attribute to this stuff. So while you should watch out for those signs just in case, I highly recommend giving this stuff a try!

column13: Another great product in this line
column14:
I started using this line of products a few months ago after reading several positive reviews. I'm 36 have always battled severe acne and discoloration. It's generally horrible. I started with just the serum, then added the cleanser, then the night cream, then the toner and then the mask.

Overall, this combination of products has drastically improved the look feel and overall health of my skin.

The night cream is very gentle and I feel does a fantastic job of healing and softening my skin. Sometimes the serum can cause minor irritation but the moisturizer really helps keep and blotches or redness in check.

I now can wear less makeup and even feel comfortable wearing my hair out of my face on a regular basis. I've never felt better about my own face and it's because I decided to invest in a line of quality products that actually works for me. I have tried several other product lines on both the mainstream cosmetic side and the natural side resulting in poor or nightmarish results.

There's something about this line that just works for me and
I'm so thankful. I may sound a little dramatic here but for me it's a big deal. Being able to actually like the skin on my face has been a big life changer for me. I recommend this line to anyone with combination and sensitive skin. It all takes a little getting used to but it's completely worth it.

column14:

Brush Heads Screw On for Easy Replacement and Cleaning

Fits Multiple Sonicare Handles

Two e-Series Standard sonic toothbrush heads and two hygienic travel caps.

column14:
Ultra Moisture Magnet Serum 50X Hyaluronic Acid has a unique non-equilibrium gel structure with gel domains that bounds the water tightly. The formula creates a film on the layer of the skin and transports this water over time. The 50X Strength of the Hyaluronic Acid makes it more potent and provides maximum water binding capacity.

One single application of this HA makes the skin look a lot younger, radiant and even-toned. Using this moisturizer/serum the skin would be dramatically plumped and lifted with incredible moisture.
This Serum is GENTLE, EFFECTIVE & SAFE for all skin types; including those with sensitive skin.

Vegan, Paraben-free, oil-free, no dyes, no fragrances or fillers, Oily Skin remedy
- Rejuvenates the look of dull skin for a smoother, more even skin tone
- Helps in fighting with the dryness /redness on face with professional hydration
- Diminishes the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles
- Fights with the dark circles under the eyes and the eye puffiness

50x Strength Hyaluronic Acid can hold 4,000 to 5,000 times its own weight in water. As it binds water to it, the individual molecules expand. This inflation of the Serum on a molecular level helps to plump the skin. It hydrates the skin and reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles and gives you a healthy, plump, smooth and glowing appearance. The amazing plumping abilities of 50 x Strength Hyaluronic Acid can be demonstrated with a dried apricot. column13: Most convenient and effective piercing infection-fighting solution I've come across!
column14:
My nose piercing, which is 10 years old, gets infected once in a while. I used to clean it with a tea tree solution but tea tree is very strong on the skin and left my skin very dry and a little darker where the infection used to be. I wanted to apply sea salt soaks to my infection since it is pretty effective but it can be messy and requires a bit of time to prepare the solution (and I have to do several soaks a day to fight the infection). I found this spray on amazon and I've been using it for almost a year now (on my second bottle now). It calms my infection really well and the best part is how convenient it is to use (compared to preparing warm sea salt soaks). I use it about 3 times a day when I have a piercing infection.

After so many years of dealing with piercing infections, I'm pretty good at knowing when an infection is about to start again and when that happens, I quickly spray this on my piercing to prevent it. It's done a pretty good job at keeping infection away almost 98% of the time.

column14: I have been trying out different natural deodorants over the years but was never fully happy. Roll ons took too long to dry, creams left white marks on my clothes or didn't quite melt well into my pits, and most gels did absolutely nothing other than maybe perfume my B.O. I happened to end up in the beauty/health section of Whole Foods and was looking at the ingredients and decided to try out this brand. If I hadn't been there to smell the actual product I would have gone with the unscented version to be safe but I REALLY love the Dusk scent. It's very Old-spicey-esque but without that weird chemically alcoholy aspect to it (plus it's not overwhelming). Most importantly of course, this stuff really works! The gel doesn't clump up in my pit hair (tmi?), it dries very quickly, and seriously does keep me smelling nice all day. I went on a hike just the other day in 90 degree super humid Virginia and I was the only one in my group who didn't smell like B.O. by the end of our 8 miles. Definitely recommend!! And this is coming from a very sweaty and stinky person. Just remember that this is NOT an antiperspirant (which isn't good for you in the first place, sweating is important for your bodily functions) so don't expect this to stop your sweat.

column14: What I like about Crest Pro Health® HD™ is that it is an easy two step system that only takes two minutes (vs. some of the whitening strips that you have to leave on for 30 minutes). You can use the tooth whitening system the way that you use your toothpaste or gel - and I like that it does not foam like crazy (I have an electric toothbrush and some toothpastes go all over the place). First you apply the purifying cleanser for one minute - do NOT rinse with water afterwards! I like the nice minty taste of it. Afterwards you apply the perfecting gel for one minute. I wished the gel was a little bit more minty - but otherwise it is good and does not irritate my gums. I cannot see that my teeth are six times whiter as promised after one week (but I use a good electronic toothbrush that usually removes stains and plaque pretty well) - but my mouth feels clean and healthy without the hassle of whitening strips and normal time involvement as I always brush for two minutes. The cost is lower compared with whitening strips and the system should last approximately two months. I like that you get a full money back guarantee if you do not like it. column6: Neutrogena Healthy Skin Blush
column13: Just the Right Amount of Glow and Color for a Subtle \Natural\" Look"
column14:
I am the type of person who thinks "Less is More" when it comes to cosmetics. At 60 years old, this is true even more than when I was young, and a subtle touch is just perfect for me. This Neutrogena Blush is light, natural and fresh looking and that is why I like it.

I ordered the Rosy color and when the package came, there was also the Bronzed and Luminous included. So I was able to try all three colors. They all go on easily and light and give the skin a glow with faint color to create a naturally beautiful look that doesn't seem overdone. Just a little "sun kissed" and nothing more. I think it is perfect.

If you are a purist when it comes to natural and non-toxic, this is probably safe enough for most people, but the ingredient list has a lot of unpronounceable ingredients. So those of us who really, REALLY want to be ABSOLUTELY NATURAL, might want to look further to get exactly the right product. If you just want something that looks nice and isn't irritating, this might be exactly the thing for you.

So if you are fond of a refined look that seems natural and not made up, you should like this. If you are used to a dramatic look, then you might not care for this particular product because it goes on light and the color is faint and almost undetectable. Just right for an "Earth Mother" but probably not enough drama for a "Beauty Queen".

column13: What a great idea and design - turns my daily face wash into a deep cleaning massage!
column14:
[[VIDEOID:ed97333a1b1f45c931af0877ac77a4f7]]When I saw this Geekable Park silicone facial massager I was really intrigued. I've never seen a product anything like this, but now that I've tried it I realize what a clever idea and design it is. The entire surface is covered in a high quality smooth silicone, with tiny hair-like bristles on the front of the paddle. The shape and the silicone material combine to make it very easy to grip and generally comfortable to hold onto during use. It's great that it recharges with the included USB cord, so there's no need to fuss with batteries. Now that I've used this, I definitely prefer washing my face with this massager. I just get my normal facial cleanser lathered up on my face as I always would, but then instead of just using my heads to rub it in, I use the Geekable Park device to get it thoroughly down into the pores. It also feels great, like a bit of a massage for my face. There are four different speeds/intensities that I can choose from by just pressing the plus and minus buttons and I also can vary if I'm using the tip of the device with the larger silicone bristles or the main part of the paddle with its tiny bristles.

It stays on for one minute, with a quick pulse after 30 seconds and a couple more pulses in the second 30 seconds to help keep track of how long I've been washing my face. If the one minute isn't long enough, it's very easy to press the button to turn it back on. The silicone is very easy to clean when I'm all done. My face ends up feeling extra clean - really the skin is softer than I'm used to!

I also feel I have to mention that I can see people wanting to use this for more intimate purposes as well. The silicone material and vibrating massage definitely make one think of an adult toy. The minute shut off timer though may be a tamper for this kind of use.

I'm very glad that I was able to receive this as a free promotional sample in order to evaluate and provide my honest review.w.

column13: A good skin care product? Probably. Has it lightened my sun spots? Nope.
column14:
I am a younger guy who has spent too much time in the sun and thus, have developed some sun spots. After vetting various products, I came to the conclusion that this product may be the ticket. After all, "customers report that age and dark spots fade" after using this product.

Well, maybe my skin is different. Maybe I had unfair expectations. However, this product has not lightened any of my sun spots at all. I am sure the product is good for my skin - it is organic, replenishes some vitamins, etc. and after use, my skin feels tight, a bit refreshed. But I bought this product not because I am worried about wrinkles, but because I want my sun spots to fade. Using this anticipated result as a benchmark, the product hasn't impressed me. I give it three stars because I think it may be a good product that is good for your skin - I just haven't had the results I am looking for.

column14:
I'm a working mom who's always on the go... I need a deodorant that can keep up because I don't have time to stop and freshen up. A couple clicks and two quick rubs under each arm and I'm good for the whole day. (And I have some really long days...)
Two hours a day, I'm watching my son in his JiuJitsu classes in a gym without air conditioning in the heat of the summer. Running from BJJ to drum lessons to piano lessons and trying to cram my own job in there is time consuming and stressful. Secret clinical strength is what I've always needed and never knew about. I don't know what I did before, but I'm not going back. It keeps me dry and smelling fresh so I can get on with life. I'd totally recommend this product!!
I received a free sample of Secret Clinical Strength deodorant as a member of One2One Network. All opinions are my own.

column6: AXE Total Fresh 3 in 1 Shampoo, Conditioner and Body Wash, Total Fresh 22 oz
column13: Are you Type A or Type B?
column14:
Most people are probably going to fall into one of two categories when it comes to products like this … A) those who believe they need individual specially formulated “products” for each act of self-grooming, i.e. soap, shampoo, conditioner, body wash, deodorant, perfumes, and so on … and B) people who don’t really care. I’ve found I am leaning more and more to the second category. I have to ask is there really that much fundamental difference between some of the products I use?

After all, it is pretty well accepted these days to combine shampoo with conditioner, right? Why not use the same product as a body wash? And most bath soaps advertise that they have deodorant properties, so why not combine that feature as well?

I like the feel and fragrance of Axe products and I have used some of their similar products before, in fact before ordering this bottle I have been using one Axe product as both shampoo and conditioner and from time to time I’ve used it as a body wash with good results.

So I like the idea … less packaging waste, less choices to make, less clashing of fragrances, and less waste. I like that the “Total Fresh” fragrance doesn’t make me smell like I fell into a tank of perfume … it is clean and goes with pretty much any occasion, such as work, visiting friends, or an evening out to dinner.

The bottom line is that cosmetics are highly personal. Whether someone here rates this product as 5-star or 1-star really doesn’t mean a thing if you don’t like it, does it? So my suggestion is that if you fit into Category B described above go ahead and get a bottle of this and try it for yourself. I can’t think of anything at all negative about it (like it doesn’t eat your skin away or turn you green or clog your drains).

If you like it, note that one of the reasons I rated it highly is that it is being sold at a fair price, not the lowest but then again Axe is a major brand name.

column6: African Black Soap - Face & Body Wash - All Natural Soap for Acne, Eczema, Psoriasis - with Shea Butter and Coconut Oil - 12 OZ
column13: who used to make me some really awesome liquid black soap
column14:
Many years ago, I had a friend from Jamaica, who used to make me some really awesome liquid black soap. I absolutely LOVED it! I never had to worry about breakouts or uneven skin texture - which was a huge deal for me as I've dealt with breakouts since I was a teenager. Sadly, Jai (my friend from Jamaica), decided to move back to his native country - and I was left without a black soap "dealer".

Being that i'd never heard of black soap before he and I were friends, I didn't know it was available to purchase. I'd never seen it in stores so I figured I was out of luck... until the magical moment I discovered it (in solid form) for sale by my favorite skincare company! Had I seen it sooner, you can bet your booty that I would have ordered it before now!

As others have stated, it's very "homemade" looking. That's a BIG positive for me. No gimmicks, no frill. There's no need for it. What they have here, is a quality product - and a LOT of it!

If you're looking at the price and thinking, "why would I pay $10-$18" for a bar a soap", keep reading...

1. Completely obliterates acne on all skin types
2. It's made with all natural ingredients! No perfumes or fillers, just honest to goodness, REAL ingredients.
3. It's MASSIVE! This isn't some rinky-dink portion. In fact, I was just telling my husband that I would gladly pay $30 for the amount of black soap you actually get. It's SO much, that I cut it up into 60 pieces. Each piece lasts me about 10 uses. That's 600 uses, WOWZA!

Once you receive your order, you'll see why I opted to cut mine into piece. It's easier to handle, and you don't get the whole thing wet when all you need is a little bit. It really does go long way.

The lather is incredible (so rich and creamy). It's really a win/win. Your face gets this amazing spa-like treatment (which effectively rids you of breakouts), while your hands are moisturized and rejuvenated.

There's a reason I adore Cleopatra's Choice. Every single product I have ever purchased from them, has been phenomenal.

I did receive this product for free in exchange for my honest review, but my opinions have in no way been swayed. I truly love the soap (along with all of their other products) and will be a customer for life! I am honestly in LOVE with this stuff!ed.

column13: A Premium High Quality Bath Body Brush That Is Built To Last!
column14:
[[VIDEOID:388ee7cb1880cba7a06f243590e816c1]]Let me start off by saying that I go through several body brushes every year. The main issue? The bristles either fall out or handle falls off. Usually within the first week or two of use! This Bath Body Brush by Regöra is not like the others I have bought at the pharmacy store. Out of the box I could tell this brush was extremely well made. I did a tension stress test on the bristles by pulling very hard on them one by one. Not one bristle fell out! That right there told me this brush was well designed and built to last. The other thing I did was pull tightly on the handle. The tongue and groove design often found on wooden handle body brushes usually don't hold up very well and can easily be pulled out. The handle on this brush did not budge at all. No wiggling or anything. I am truly impressed!

The handle has a nice rubber texturized grip which is perfect for when your hands are all soapy in the bath or shower and you are using body wash or other soap...the brush will not slip out of your hands. There is a nice comfortable handle attached to the main brush for extra convenience.

Overall I am very satisfied with this body brush and the Regöra brand!

****UPDATE**** 8/23/2015

Previously I had stated that the brush and handle seemed to be tightly in place. I know that this brush had the feature of being able to detach from the handle, but to be honest didn't think of it because I have owned many other brushes where the handle is too easily detachable and makes the brush nearly useless. However, recently I wanted to use the brush for my feet, and the handle was cumbersome so I wanted to detach it. I noticed that others have had similar issues so here is a video on how to safely detach it without damaging the strap or brush. The video is short, but it shows that if you firmly grasp the main brush and wiggle it and pull out the handle at the same time, it does remove. After the first time it isn't so hard to detach, it's just the initial detaching that is a bit snug. Hope this helps!es remove. After the first time it isn't so hard to detach, it's just the initial detaching that is a bit snug. Hope this helps!

column6: Shea Butter & Malawi Sugar 2-n-1 Body Scrub (Almond Milk)
column14:
I love this product. I am so sorry I have run out of it. I am on a cosmetics and skincare "no buy" right now but as soon as that is over, I am getting more of this.

I use scrubs often and this one has been gentle enough to use daily. I focus on areas of rough skin, particularly my upper arms. The concentration of scrubbing particles is perfect and the cream formulation keeps them on your skin (and working) for longer. They don't rinse off down the drain until you actively try to rinse them off. A side effect of this is that you don't have to use a ton of this at once, so the container lasts a long time.

This smells heavenly. Of course I love anything almond scented. I love that it doesn't contain any plastic like some other scrubs I've used lately (exfoliation comes from volcanic stone and sugar, and you can see the ingredients list a bit down on the product page).

I rarely gush about products. But this is seriously one of my favorite discoveries this year (random purchase with Birchbox points).

You clean your face but are you getting everything removed completely? User error or product lacking, but not all cleansers, in fact most of them, do not clean my face as completely as needed the first time. Just look at the towel after you wash your face..how can there still be makeup on the towel?

This is where toners come into your cleansing routine. Toners are used to remove any makeup and dirt after you can cleaned your face with a cleanser. Using a toner will help to soften the skin and clean off any soap residue that was not dissolved by rinsing, along with any remaining makeup left on your face.

Since using the toner along with my other daily skincare products (cleanser, serum, and a moisturizer) I have noticed a difference in the feel and look of my skin. Even in my mid-fifties I suffer from an occasionally flare-up of blemishes.

column13: I am very glad to have found a Pine oil that not adulterated
column14:
I am very glad to have found a Pine oil that not adulterated. I have read somewhere before that pine essential oil is one of those oils that are frequently adulterated and Turpentine is used as an inexpensive filler. That sounds scary, right? Plant Therapy gives me a peace of mine that the oil I am using is One hundred percent certified pure therapeutic grade essential oil. It has no fillers, additives, bases or carriers added.

Pine essential oil is a very relaxing oil It is great for after exercising. But never use it without a carrier oil because the skin can get irritated.

This pine is also great for diffusing. It gives out a very relaxing scent.

This pine essential oil is also great to make a home made gel air freshener. Just go get you a unflavored gelatine, water and some salt, then add some of this essential oil, and you will have your very own home made gel freshener (pls. use google for recipes).

Overall, I am very happy that I was choosen to test and review this pine essential oil. I can really say that it's a very high quality oil. Plant therapy has not failed me yet. I am so far very impressed with their oils and I highly recommend it to all of my family and friends.

column13: This shaver is great! It shaves closer than my Gillette fusion
column14: This shaver is great! It shaves closer than my Gillette fusion. Some spots you have to go over more than others but it is a quick shave and the self cleaner is great although it does take a very long time. I always hated electric razors because they would cut my neck this one does not have this issue. I believe it has the fastest motor on the market. The only issue I have is it shaves so close that I develope ingrown hairs on my chin and the sides of my mouth. I am 36 and looked like a 16 year old after I shaved. After 2 months of use, I do switch and use the Gillette every other time to help the ingrown hair problem it is not nearly as bad. It definitely takes a little time for your face to adjust. I have to shave often and it really is unbelievable how soft my face is after using this razor. It is expensive but when you consider an 8 pack of Gillette blades are about 40 dollars it will pay for itself in a couple years. I'd highly recommend this razor.

column6: Miraqueen Professional Curling Iron, Curling Wand, Hair Curler with Ceramic Curling Chamber
column13: great curler, worth the cost if you curl your hair often
column14: Great hair curler, but I had to wait 5 months for it to be back in stock prime and the regular price ($89.99) since Christmas 2014. The curler itself works well. It beeps at you if you put in too much hair (for me about 1 inch width is the max). I have long straight thick hair and it curls it well, though some curls have to be redone by the time I am done. It takes approximately 35-40 minutes to curl all my hair, pinning it up and curling it by layers. I use Shea Moisture shampoo and conditioner and the oils in these do not cause my hair to burn. It is virtually impossible to burn yourself with it unlike regular hair wand curlers, and this doesn't entail wrapping or twisting. My hair got stuck a few times but it was easy to ease it out and did not get split or cut up.  I use organic sweet almond oil as frizz control and heat protectant with this curler, and I have heard that avocado oil works well as heat protectant with it too. I haven't needed a hair spray to hold the curls, though I recommend Herbal Essence flexible hold hair spray because of its ingredients.

column6: The Honest Company Honest Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30 2-pack 3.0oz
column14:
I am a longtime user of mineral sunscreen, and this is the worst one I've ever used. First, the product is extremely greasy and oily coming out of the package. It almost seems like pure oil. I suspect that it separates inside the bottle, and that might be why it doesn't work well. Because it definitely does not work--my very fair family all got lightly burned within 1 hour using this sunscreen at a non-water non-sweaty activity. I'd say the protection it gives is approximately like a typical spf 5 "suntan lotion". Nothing like a SPF 30 block should be! I'm thankful that we did a trial run at a short activity, because a day at the beach could have ended us up at the doctor if Honest Company was all we had to rely on!

Most mineral sunscreens have downsides, the most effective ones being very thick and leaving your whole skin with a whitish cast. I think the happy medium for me is Mexitan spf 30. perfect ingredient list, decent results, workably thin consistency so it doesn't take all day to lotion up. At first glance this seemed like a better deal, but both bottles are going in the trash. I can pay twenty bucks for a huge 8 ounce bottle that lasts all summer if I know it will protect my family.

column6: The Honest Company Honest Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30 2-pack 3.0oz
column13: Not a single sunburn for a super pale family
column14: I'm rather suspicious of all the people who've claimed they got horrible burns even when using this. Not like they are liars, but maybe they didn't actually know how to apply physical sunscreens- they don't work the same way as your name brand chemically sunscreens at all. First of all, this is a physical sunscreen, not the scary chemical kind. Physical sunscreens require that you put a thick layer on- you can't use a thin veil and think it will do anything. That's true of all natural sunscreen brands, as a matter of fact. Second, and most important for my pale family, you have to actually follow directions. The bottle says you have to reapply every x hours, how can you expect a good result if you never reapply? This sunscreen protected my pale family (so pale my sister mixes the lightest color of foundations with a good amount of goth targeted pure white costume foundation to make it actually match her real skin color) at the beach, the pool, and the amusement park. My sister is severely allergic to most every kind of sunscreen- all mainstream and even most all natural and organic and baby formulations can close up her airways so she can't breathe and swell up her face so she's unrecognizable- and she loves the beach and she's super pale, so we have tried and vetted out 100's of different sunscreens over the years to try to find the perfect brand. This isn't that, because we live in a humid area and it sometimes makes sweat form little droplets on top of my skin instead of letting it evaporate well and that feels really clammy and gross when the air is already syrup, but it works perfectly as a sunscreen and is super moisturizing to the skin so I am definitely keeping it for trips to drier climates, like when I visit Colorado or California or really anywhere besides the South. In other good news, we left a bottle in the car on a day when the asphalt was melting while we went to the amusement park (another was in the pack so we could reapply every now and then) andthe bottle didn't become gross and liquidy like name brand chemical lotions do- Banana Boat, Coppertone, and the like get gross and melty in the sun, which is ridiculous considering it is made to be used in the Summer when it gets hot, and also because it's chemically so the whole world of nonmelting ingredients is open to them- but anyways Honest sunscreen doesn't get gross in the bottle, it also doesn't feel super cold when you put it on like other brands do, it works for super pale people with infrequent reapplication (5-8 hours though that's beyond bottle recommended time) in thick layers but it didn't look stark white once we rubbed it in, and it left my arms so incredibly and wonderfully smooth and moisturized. It does rub off a little bit once it's first applied though so a little bit got on the back of the leather car seats from my shoulder, so put a towel there or something if it bothers you.

column13: Probably great for guys with softer beard.
column14:
How do I know if I have a tough or easy beard to shave? I just assumed I was average, whatever that was. So I chose these as they were in the middle of sharpness from less to more. You can spend more to get much sharper blades.

Since I was new to shaving this way I had to make a guess. I wish I had asked my barber, because as it turns out he would know, right? I am light complected with light hair on arms and face. That does NOT mean I don't have a coarse beard. These blades just don't cut it well, and I have to shave twice. Barber tells me that relative to hundreds of dudes he's felt their face that mine is fairly coarse so I'll have to find a sharper blade. I have to use way too much pressure to get these to cut, so next time instead of 100 pack I'll order a variety pack to be sure of what type I need.

Blade lasts about 4 shaves, shaving twice each time, before I feel I need to replace.

column13: Love the fragrance and quality of this Rosemary Essential Oil
column14:
I'm very pleased with this pure Rosemary Essential Oil's quality and aroma, and the manufacturer is right about it being more concentrated than others I've purchased before. It's delightful woodsy minty scent is every bit as lovely as the rosemary I clipped from my garden but even more powerful, so this 10ml bottle should last me a while since I don't need to use as much of this in my home made cream and shampoo as I used to use with the brands I bought before.

This Avían' Botanicals Rosemary Essential Oil is 100% pure, undiluted, not combined with carrier oils or any other extender, is highly concentrated, and comes with a dropper so it's easy to measure out the exact amount of drops you need. It's perfect for adding to my home made whipped Shea Butter skin cream, because Rosemary is a powerful antioxidant with the same free radical fighting power as goji berries! Here's my recipe for those of you interested in making your own all natural anti-aging moisturizer cream as well:

Whipped Shea Butter Lotion
4 oz. Pure raw unrefined organic shea butter
2 Tbsp Fractionated Coconut Oil
7 drops of Carrot Essential Oil
7 drops of Avíano Botanicals Rosemary Essential Oil
Mixing Bowl - (I use my Ninja to mix and whip rather than a bowl and hand mixer)
Mixer
2 clean and empty 4 oz jars with lid liners

How to make it:
1. Have Raw Unrefined Shea Butter at room temperature (Do not melt or heat it!)
2. Measure 4oz and add that to Ninja and pulse - (or to a bowl - if done in a bowl mash it with a fork like you would whipped potatoes)
3. Add 2 Tbsp Fractionated Coconut Oil & pulse (or mash) a little more
4. Blend in Ninda for approx. 2 minutes (or mix on high speed for about 5 minutes if doing in bowl) until mixture is creamy and well blended
5. Put whipped lotion into clean jars and close. Store in clean, dry, dark and cool place. Room temperature is generally fine.

Besides being high in antioxidants, Rosemary Essential Oil natural carnosol which lower DHT and improves hair growth. Regular use of rosemary oil helps to stimulate follicles, making hair grow longer and stronger. You can use this therapeutic grade premium Rosemary as an additive to you shampoo, conditioner, as a scalp treatment, a leave in conditioner, or use it to make your own shampoo.

Here's a recipe for a lovely Rosemary Peppermint Shampoo that makes 8 ounces.
•6 oz Aloe Vera Gel
•3 Tbsp Olive Oil
•10 Tbsp Baking Soda
•20 drops Rosemary Oil
•10 drops Peppermint Oil

You can experiment with the number of drops you prefer, the carrier oil, and even change the Peppermint out for a different essential oil if you prefer. column6: JOVANA Women Zipper Closure Small Cosmetic Case Makeup Bag (Red)
column13: Easy to clean toiletry tote or makeup case.
column14:
The other half bought this specifically for a tampon case. She wanted something she could toss in an overnight, gym, or carry on bag and have all of her 'monthly needs' met. While she wasn't thrilled about the material at first (it's rather shiny nylon build,) the plush woven hex cross pattern adds a little more luxury to the case, overall. It's actually quite spacious. Jenna used some felt and a fabric pen to give it a little tongue and cheek face-lift to suit her style.

Pros:

*Decent size- Holds 20 regular (non compact) size tampons with room for personal wipes and a few thin pads. Despite the lining of the case being plush, the weight of the case is almost non existent and it very easily stashes away.

*This case stands up on it's own, with a flat bottomed design.

*The zipper has held up over a considerable amount of use over several months and seems to close securely. We like that the zipper color matches the bag, itself.

*There is a little loop on one end to tether it to a larger cosmetics case, or simply grab with a few fingers and go.

*The material is very easy to clean and resistant to makeup smudges.

Cons:

*This is a soft case- do not expect it to protect your valuables, and we would not recommend it for expensive makeup compacts, as it can be crushed.

We paid more than the current $5 asking price for this case and still considered it a good deal as it is spacious and very durable with nice stitching.

column6: Cover Your Gray Brush In Wand (Pack of 6) Dark Brown
column14:
Ok, I admit I have one or two gray hairs in my beard. Maybe more than one or two on a bad day. Ok, maybe more like one or two gray patches in my beard. I can admit that anonymously on Amazon, but I'm not going to admit that out in public in front of friends and coworkers and all.

That’s where Cover Your Gray comes in.

I tried another product that is Just For Beards. It burned and irritated my skin, made my non-gray hair too dark, and looked terrible a few days later.

And then I found Cover Your Gray! The package shows woman applying it to her hair, but I can't imagine anyone would have the patience to paint her hair with this little brush.

But it's almost perfect for beards. 20 seconds in the morning and my gray beard is GONE! A quick touch-up after lunch and I'm young and handsome all day.

I'd give it 5 stars if it were waterproof and if it didn't smudge the collar of my winter coat. But even so, I don't walk out of my apartment without checking my beard and touching it up with Cover Your Gray if needed.

column13: Hard to apply, gives very little control, and rubs off. Other Anastasia brow products are a better buy.
column14: I really wanted to love this product after reading so many positive reviews on it online and seeing so many makeup bloggers recommend it, but it just wasn't my cup of tea. The color I purchased based upon the info on the Anastasia website should have been a perfect match, but it was WAY too dark. You have to use a very light hand with this product to keep it from getting too dark and too fake looking. But therein lies the rub: the whole concept of a "pomade" is that it is supposed to provide color and control, acting as a brow tint or powder and a control wax. But in order to get the color right with this product I have to use so little that it provides no control and I end up reaching for my trusty NYX wax pencil anyway. column14:
I got this from here, but on my husbands account! :)

I've been wanting to try this for ages, since I found it surfing for things to help my nails recover from acrylics. My nails were a bit iffy before, but after they pretty much got worse, and my regular lotion/nail moisturizers didn't seem to be cutting it.

I REALLY wish that I took pictures before I started, but my nails would show every singly little crease and crack from spots peeling and whatnot. After the first application, after a few minutes I could feel a few of my nails seemed to tighten. I didn't do the 3 day hydration thing, I'm just doing it intermittently throughout the day when I'm going to be sitting for a while, and I avoid "rubbing" it in (I just feel that everything I put on my nail is just going to get soaked up by my finger!), and after about 30 min~an hour my nails are all soaked up and shiny!

After two days now, my nails feel far more stronger than they were. NO more showing of any peeling/cracks, and even on one of my thumb nails where there was a small bit of nail peeling up, has seemed to fuse back down. I will of course be trimming off all the old growth and let the new growth with the help of this oil!

So far, so good! I'm certainly impressed with it. I won't be using it VERY much after I get my nails in good shape, maybe a few bare soaks a few times a week, defiantly will pick up some more! :)

column6: CREED Millesime Imperial Unisex Spray, 4-Fluid Ounce
column14:
So Creeds are a bit tricky when it comes to grey market. They change their packaging and bottles often and this is probably compounded more due to the fact that most bottles come from the Middle East hence the Arabic insert. With all that said the product I recieved from Amazon seems to be legit. The bottle/packaging has the Batch number of LT3314G01 33 is the number assigned to Millesime Imperial and the 14 is year of production. Another thing Creed is notorious for is batch variation, meaning some batches have more prominent notes than others and some have better or worse longevity. So that why some samples or older bottles may conflict with this purchase. Obviously if it doesn't smell similar then that's a different story but if it overall is similar you're good to go.

I get poor longevity from this fragrance (about 3-4 hours) and it doesn't project much. That said it's an amazing fragrance, the sea salt and fruit (I say watermelon like most) create such an intoxicating summer feeling I just wish it lasted longer (I carry a decant for backup). I'd recommend it to both males and females looking for a different type of summer scent that isn't aquatic or citrus based.

column6: G&W Heel Lift - Clearly Adjustable - Sold Individually
column14: As I just spent the last 2 years walking a pair of these off, to the point of destruction, I feel competent to give a fair minded review. First, they do work...They more than make up for the shortness in one leg that I have to contend with. Second, they are well made and tough. Forget those spongy lifts that will feel great at first but compress over time. I need firm support to avoid stressing my Left hip by compensating for my shortened leg when walking. These put me on an even keel with every stride and eliminates my hip pain completely.  I'm agnostic on the benefits of these lifts being adjustable. Personally, I'd much rather have a solid one piece support that comes in the 3/8 to 5/8 inch (ideal) size that I need. Perhaps they should expand their line of products by offering solid lifts in a variety of sizes.  The problem with these multi-layer adjustable supports is the layers can start to shift by themselves over time. It may take a while but it will eventually happen. It does make me wonder if I wouldn't be better off planing a piece of hard wood or plastic to achieve the same end for a lifetime lift that would never wear out. And a solid lift would be much easier to clean between shoes.  A solid lift would also minimize the mold that tends to form between the layers after months and months of being exposed to your living, breathing and sweating feet all day. Even placed under a foot pad, these lifts will eventually funk up on you. And if, like me, you care to remove them for use in other shoes, these multiple layers will start to loose their natural adhesion and tackiness. Which is another reason they'll start shifting on you over time.  Hence, my rather mediocre rating. Yes, they do work. They feel great when new. And they gave me 2 years of faithful service before giving out.  Maybe expecting a lifetime of service is asking too much. But it wouldn't be a great chore for this company to fuse these layers into a solid form and they jolly well would last a lifetime. Or a decade or more.. I'd pay extra for that kind of dependability. And of course, the sheer utility of being able to use them in a variety of shoes in my closet in a pinch would be a great improvement.

column6: Fogless Shower Mirror
column14:
It's a great product that will last for ~2 years, but is a hassle to remove (and sometimes causes damages.) I've owned three of them over the past ~5 years and can now write a pretty comprehensive review.

Let's start with the good. Shaving in the shower is great, and this product makes it super easy. The set up is easy and while it isn't super clear, it works more than well enough to shave with. The company also will send free mounting kits if you decide to move.

Now the bad. Over time, the mirror becomes less clear (but still usable.) The tilting mechanism wears out in a few years which is the biggest flaw. Once filled with water, there is no way to position it between the middle setting and the bottom setting without it 'falling'. I contacted ToiletTree and was ignored. Last, it is advertised as removable but be cautious. I've mounted it on tile and twice on plastic. The second time on plastic is bonded so well (and the plastic was so weak) that it ripped a huge hole in the shower wall. My landlord will not be happy.

column13: Get clean, smell great and enjoy mild exfoliation with lots of lather!!
column14:
We LOVE this soap and are so happy to have found it on Amazon. My husband has eczema and we have tried many natural soaps and body washes but this, in our experience, has exceeded them all.
If used alone, it is a mild exfoliant due to the presence of the sea salt. It's wonderful to have this option in the soap rather than having to rely on another source for exfoliation. When we just want the creamy and abundant suds it provides we use a nylon scrubby. We have found that the bars last much longer with this method since you only need to give the soap a few passes over the scrubby to have more than enough lather to shower with.
As it says on the box it is great for shaving. The lather is so creamy! And the smell is divine!! It smells fresh, that's the only way I can describe it, which makes it great for both of us to use. No more multitude of his & her products in our small shower!!
If you're looking for a great way to get clean, smell great and avoid the plethora of chemicals found in most shower/bath products give this a try. It also makes a great gift...I'm always tucking one in a gift bag for someone and then I hear 'I love it...where can I buy it?'
Enjoy!

column6: Herbal Essences Color Me Vibrant Permanent Hair Color 016 Knockout Blonde
column14:
This is far and away my favorite hair coloring. You couldn't find it for a stretch there, and I was buying it from off merchants when I could find it, and now I'm so excited to see that Amazon is selling it again.

My hair is naturally what I've long called dirty dishwater strawberry blond and a friend more poetically called the color of honey. It's a reddish dark blond or maybe a light auburn, but isn't a fiery carrot top of any shade. For me, this covers (or disguises?) the gray that's creeping in and kicks up the red a bit.

When I was unable to find this and trying to find "my shade" in other brands (hopeless), I was always embarrassed to be near other people just after a coloring because it all stinks so much. Not to mention what the hell am I doing to myself with those harsh chemicals. (For some brands, the included conditioner smells like fake coconut and that's a smell I particularly detest; the conditioner here is more of a neutral scent.)

This won't be for everyone because it's not "permanent", but for me, I like that it gradually fades out and doesn't leave a line with the new growth. And I also like that it doesn't make my hair a monotone color... it adds color and leaves natural variation, and I think the result is very natural looking. For me, I try not to leave it on too long or it ends up a little redder than I'd like most of the time.

FWIW, I have very long hair but just use one box. I do all the wrong things and color just after shampooing, so my hair is still wet from that. Plus, of course, the ends don't need much.

column14:
This lotion works well -- absorbing quickly, and moisturizing without leaving skin feeling greasy. The scent is a delightful cranberry with citrus undertones, which is very pleasant but not overwhelming and reminds me of Thanksgiving and happy holidays. The scent lasts just long enough but the moisturizing lasts much longer. I use this primarily as a body lotion after showering, but prefer the matching hand cream for my hands since it is thicker and more moisturizing -- which my dry hands really need, although if your hands are not too dry, this would also be good for routine hand moisturizing.

I often use this lotion after a bath with the matching bath soak (which was a disappointing purchase, by the way). This lotion would not work as well for extremely dry skin, like in the winter -- the body butter is better suited for that. Overall, an effective moistuzing lotion, at a good price, especially with the subscribe & save discount. Plus, it is made in Canada of natural ingredients. Highly recommended!

column6: Fusion Beauty Lipfusion Pencil
column14: My wife has been using this product for years, but she does not use it as a straight lipstick, because that really does not work.  So this is what she does: At night, she uses the LIPFUSION XL (she has decided that the XXL is not as good, but the XL is fantastic).  She puts on a heavy coat each night before bed, and that keeps the lips hydrated and plumped (over time you will notice a difference).  For her daytime routine, she uses a lip liner (Urban Decay from Sephora), then a lipstick of choice (she likes Clinque long lasting, but any lipstick will work), and then uses this LipFusion pencil over the lipstick.  It adds color to your lipstick, so you need to figure out how the colors blend, but it provides additional plumping for daytime.  It will not last if you eat, and you will need to reapply.  Overall, the LipFusion pencils are easy to use, soft enough to apply, and come with a sharpener that works well.  A good addition to your daily routine.

column6: HOT SHOT SLIMMING GEL & MASSAGING GEL
column14:
After having my kids, I had a bit of a belly left over. I worked on dropping weight, which wasn't too hard. 45 lbs later, I realized that it was not the weight that was as much of an issue as the skin that was left after dropping all the weight. I have been working on toning, but needed a little extra help. I tried out the hot shot gel, and immediately noticed the menthol ish type smell and feel on my skin. The gel is easy to use, you don't need a ton. I spread it all over my belly and waited for it to dry. There was no sticky residue left after, just a very tingly feeling. Almost like I had been working out, then cooling down. The skin already looks better. Over all it is helpful and I can't wait to see how I look in a few months as I keep up with exercising and using my hot shot gel. I love that is'a 87% organic. I would love to see it 100%.

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT TO TRY AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE IN EXCHANGE FOR AN HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW. ALL OPINIONS ARE MY OWN

column6: 1000 Hour Eyelash & Brow Dye / Tint Kit Permanent Mascara
column14:
perfect, works great. Lasted for 4 weeks, and it was still on my lashes, but I reapplied after 4 weeks for the new eyelash growth. Easy to use, does not irritate my eyes at all, washes off skin with just water. I've been using blue-black, will try black next.

Some pointers:
-- when you start mixing it, it's all lumpy and separate, seems like it will never blend and mix together properly. I was sure that I did something wrong. But after mixing for a few minutes it all blended just fine, just keep mixing.
-- the color of the mixture is not what it will look like on your eyelashes. Mine looked quite purple, I was worried that I will have purple eyelashes. Nope, the eyelashes came out just fine, black with just a hint of bluishness
-- I used vaseline under my eyes the first time I used it, but I think I got some on the tips of my lower lashes and didn't dye the tips. So the second time I used no vaseline. the few smudges that I got on my skin came out just fine with a moist q-tip, I don't think there is any need for vaseline
-- it comes with a plastic stick wand and a mascara wand, I use both

overall, awesome!
