column6: Radha Beauty Rosehip Oil 4 oz - USDA Certified Organic 100% Pure Cold Pressed
column13: Color and smell is not right.
column14: I received this rosehip oil for free to try and review; regardless this is my 100% honest opinion. I am usually impressed with Radha's various products, but this rosehip oil has me thinking and wondering if it truly is rosehip oil. It is a very pale yellow color, and just barely it is very close to clear. Everything I've read in natural beauty and essential oil books say that that rosehip oil should be a rich amber color. Other brands I have are the amber color as well making me wonder why this one is sooo light. It also has absolutely no scent to it at all. The other brands have an earthy scent to them, and the books say that it should have a strong scent. I've marked it down because of the smell and color. The oil itself hasn't irritated my skin at all and I will use it in some of my beauty products I create, but I'm not sure that I would purchase it again because I'm not sure of it being the right oil in the bottle. It is a much larger sized bottle for a lower price than many other brands. The bottle itself is a blue glass and comes with a regular lid. It also comes with a glass dropper lid that you can exchange it for if you prefer droppers for your uses.

column6: Ultra-Moisturizing, Award-Winning, Blissful Body Butter with Essential Sea Oils & Pure Shea Butter by Coastal Salt & Soul
column13: AMAZING body butter, made by a very odd company
column14:
I've had a strange history with the Coastal Salt & Soul brand. I received samples of this last year to do product testing, and I absolutely loved all of it - but I adored the body butter in this scent. Just adored it.

Now when a company is going to introduce a product to the market, you'd think that they'd WANT people to buy it. I never saw a company like this one in my life. Emails, Facebook probes, even phone calls, all ignored. Me: "When will you be selling it?" Them: "Uhhhh...." Me: "Where will I be able to buy it?" Them: "Ummmm...."

The company is uber artsy-fartsy (though to give them credit, many of their things are beautiful.) I just thought they were trying to make this super exclusive, so that you had to go to a high end story in Manhattan to have a snooty saleswoman decide if she deigned to sell it to you.

Imagine my surprise when I tripped over this on Amazon. Hmmm, snooty, eh? I didn't care. I was going to buy it on Amazon initially, because there were several sellers who were selling it at a good, discounted price. Well, apparently they slumming on Amazon, but not when it came to the PRICE. The initial sellers and their good prices disappeared, and all we've got now are the high end price. Hmmm.

Oh, what the heck, I loved the body butter, so I figured I'd go for it (and I did, but not here. I found the discount sales folks, and bought it for a third less.)

Now to the product: it is probably the best body butter I've ever used. The scent is utterly unique...it kind of smells like a combination of beach campfire and sea air (yeah, that sounds strange, but this really isn't like any other scent I've ever smelled. it's totally addictive.) The body butter sinks into your skin and moisturizes it for an entire day. Come back in 24 hours, and your skin will feel like you just put it on.

Oh, and the frosted glass jar it comes in is gorgeous. The top looks like whitewashed driftwood. The box is also amazing - like I said, whoever does the art for this company has excellent taste. The body butter is amazing stuff, but the entire presentation of it in the jar and the box makes it a gift you'd be thrilled to give to anyone you adore. It really is that good.

And that's the other thing that gets me. This body butter IS worth the price they're asking (but of course, who pays full price if they don't have to?) What I don't get is why there are so many suspicious reviews on this. So many reviews from people all in the middle of July, many of them having reviewed nothing BUT this body butter (oh, and the other scent - so why are they reviewing both? They spent $90 on two jars of body butter??) And not one that I've seen actually BOUGHT the body butter from Amazon.

You usually get the scammy reviews from dubious sellers with inferior products. This body butter is absolute top of the line. I don't get why they would NEED to sham it. Like I said, it's a really weird company that just happens to make a great product. If you're a skincare junkie like me, you'll be thrilled. It's a five star product, with one off for the exceptional weirdness of the company that makes it.

P.S. One other thing: they make a luxurious bar of soap; again, one of the nicest bars of soap I've ever used. It's also being sold on Amazon, and it's also incredibly expensive at two bars for $24; if you google around, you can find it for a lot less (it only comes in two-bar boxes, one bar with this scent, and the peony one.)ewashed driftwood. The box is also amazing - like I said, whoever does the art for this company has excellent taste. column6: Ultrax Labs Hair Surge | Caffeine Hair Loss Hair Growth Stimulating Shampoo
column13: It has had the OPPOSITE effect that it was designed to have for me
column14:
This Ultrax hair shampoo has been a disaster for me. I want to start this by saying that my experience is not necessarily what your experience will be. If the 5 star reviews are to be trusted, this has worked extremely well for some people.

However, it has been worse than ineffective for me. I have been losing hair for 3 years at a steady, but noticeable rate. My scalp was started to really show to the right and left side of my slight widow's peak, along the slope where the top of my head meets the side of my head.

I started using Ultrax a few months ago, and I immediately saw a change after using it... within a week, about 25% of my hair had fallen out along this area of my head. My logic to keep with it was that, like monoxidil, caffeine would be increasing the blood flow to my follicles. This can cause hair that is in a certain stage (starved of enough nutrients) to fall out, which will normally then be replaced by new, healthier hair follicles. However, months later, no new hair has grown back.

In fact, 50% of the hair that I started with in the aforementioned areas has fallen out. It is my worst nightmare. I've finally stopped it altogether because it is now clear this product is not only NOT helping, but it is making it significantly worse. Basically, if I were to judge my hair loss in the last three years, I'd say that I lost 3 more years of hair in the span of 3 months.

I wanted everyone to be aware that... somehow - I don't know how... this product can have the reverse effect of what it is designed to do. I am a health 27 year old male, and am active, and no one on my mother's side of the family has hair-loss issues (supposedly mother's side is where we get hair-loss genes). So I may be the extremely unlucky case here.

Just because this happened to me doesn't necessarily mean this will happen to you, and that you shouldn't buy this product. Please don't let me destroy this product for you. But also, please keep my results in mind.

I am also a big diy person.  I also read where you can put a few drops of tea tree oil with 20-40 drops of witch hazel and make your own acne treatment! I am trying that as well.  Putting a few drops in your shampoo can be a lice repellent.  Also you can use it as a natural way to relieve sunburns.  Trust me when I tell you this is a great product. column6: TRESemmé Expert Selection Flexi Bounce Mousse, Youth Boost 8.1 oz
column13: Not spectacular, but my hair is nice and shiny when I use this.
column14:
Yeah, the Youth Boost is working! I'm 72 and now my hair doesn't look a day older than 69!! Seriously, though, if you shampoo and style your hair every day this product is probably going to be just as good for you as other mousse hair styling products. At first it is a little hard to know how much to use and that isn't helped by the fact that I get a different amount of mousse in my hand each time I press the dispenser. I'm hoping that will even out as I use more of the product out of the can because I feel I am wasting a good bit -- I seriously don't need all the mousse that is being dispensed right now but it is so hard to control.

I apply the mousse to towel dried hair and work it through before combing. I like to allow my hair to dry naturally, but for the first time using this product I did use a hair dryer. There was definitely more volume when my hair was dry and it actually was quite a bit softer. I don't shampoo every day so now I just allow my hair to air dry each time. I get exactly the same results with and without a hair dryer. Unfortunately, the added volume seems to only stay in my hair for the first day. The softness stays really well and the mousse isn't causing my hair to become oily between shampoos. I do not notice any particular scent, but since I have just finished using a tea tree oil shampoo which has a wonderful minty smell, I might not notice anything from the Tresemme unless it was just overpowering.

Overall I will definitely use the remainder of the product in this can and buy another to have it as a "sometimes use" alternative to the product I use most often. The container is very stylish looking with the combination of the black and lavender colors so it looks nice sitting out on the vanity. Really, this works as well as any regular hold strength mousse I've used before. A nice addition to my product shelf.

I am very happy with this product! I have been having a problem with my hair breaking a lot lately. I recently lost a very good friend and the stress and shock from that has caused my hair to break and fall out. I have fine, thin hair to begin with. So I decided I better invest in some good products before I end up bald, lol (way too young to be bald).

I was very skeptical of this particular product based on reviews of it being fake. So as soon as I got it, I took it (along with the shampoo) to my stylist. She verified that this is the actual product, as is the shampoo I bought ( Kerastase Resistance Bain Force Architecte Reconstructing Shampoo, 8.5 Ounce Sold by: Beauty Aid Essentials). She even used it when she washed my hair. She works at Regis now, and they don't carry this product, but other salons she has worked at do. But she said for my hair condition, these were the best products to use.

After using this and the shampoo for a few days, my hair is super soft, shiny, and healthy looking! I have noticed much fewer strands of hair in the drain and the brush! I am very happy with these products. They have saved my hair! Thank you Kerastatse!!!

column13: A high quality nail clipper with a smooth action.
column14:
These are a classy looking, brushed stainless steel, set of fingernail clippers. I appreciate that they are made of stainless steel, as in a humid bathroom metal that is not is prone to rusting. The brushed look is modern and sleek, though I don't often look for modern and sleek in my fingernail/toenail clippers, I will admit, it is a nice touch. What I do look for though is that these have a file in them, and I do like that. At first I had a difficult moment finding it, because it wasn't in the same place as many other files on fingernail clippers, it is not a separate slide out piece, rather it is a little file on the underside of the main lever. Its actually a better quality file than I am used to seeing on these clippers as well, which is nice. In a pinch I could use it for more than just the occasional hangnail.
This item is high quality and I was glad to have the chance to review it.

column14: My hair has always been relatively healthy and long (the middle of my back). I did a bit of research on the web and found several positive reviews about Tropic Isle Castor Oil. I apply to my scalp the evening before I go to get my hair wash; I wrap it or tie it down with a scarf, go to asleep. The following day my beautician washes it out (I use Alter Ego Garlic Shampoo). It took 3 treatments (3 Saturdays) but I noted a major difference; my scalp was no longer flaky and was growing at faster rate.  Once a month I now use castor oil as a scalp treatment.  My only advise is to add it only to the scalp and not the actual hair.

column13: This lotion is my only body lotion now.
column14:
I have a capricious and sensitive skin that reacts to lot of chemicals that are routinely added to cosmetics. I live in the UK and this lotion is not widely available, but I thought I would give it a go. Got it from amazon.com, paid VAT and delivery costs and hoped it was worth it.

It was worth it. Things I like:

- It is natural. No nasty chemicals and upset my skin.
- It is not greasy. It absorbs very well and you only need a little. The bottle will last a while.
- You don't need to apply it very often. Once your dryness settles, you will probably need occasional applications.
- It makes my skin feel very silky and smooth.

Things to watch: It has a very pleasant but initially noticeable smell, which comes from natural ingredients. I like it and like to smell it on my clothes, but if you are very smell sensitive or highly allergic, have a test first.

And one more thing - the team that created the lotion was very helpful. A big thank you to them.

column6: MapofBeauty 32\ /80cm Side Bangs Long Spiral Curly Cosplay Costume Wig (Blonde/Yellow)"
column14: I bought the wig labeled "Blonde"; it is an orange-yellow, sort of vibrant marigold color- very true to the picture and EXACTLY what I wanted. Don't be confused by the name, it looks nothing like natural blonde hair- and again, that's what I had hoped for. Other reviews had left me skeptical that the wig would look like the picture, but if you're like me then let me put your fears to rest because yes, it IS that intense sunflower color with mac n' cheese orange mixed in, and it is lovely. As for quality and fullness, the front has plenty of hair between the bangs and regular bits but the back is a little thin. To be fair, the only time I noticed the wig cap was when I was moving around a lot or when I split it into handfuls for a potential braid, but it's something to keep in mind. If you're going to be wearing something on your head over it though you will be fine. And for my needs wearing it once or twice with a costume, especially since I struggled to find another wig in a similar color at a reasonable price, it's not a deal breaker for me. Just something to consider if you're looking for a wig for a long-term project over a costume that's a lark. And one more thing, the wig does come in standard size with little straps inside to make it smaller, but something I didn't see anyone mention is that the straps are not adjustable. You either fit the standard no-straps size, or you fit the tighter "size" with the straps. That's it. Not an issue for me, but something to think about if you're buying this for maybe a child or someone with a smaller head.

column6: TOOGOO(R) Bronze Retro Compact/Travel/Pocket ILLUMINATED Beauty Make up Mirrors New
column13: Pretty disappointing even at a low price point
column14:
I was very disappointed in these mirrors because the pictures make them look terrific. I realize they are low priced, but they are about the same price as other ones that I have purchased and are not even close to the same quality. In fact, it takes SO long to get these that I ended up buying other ones and getting them way before these finally showed up. However, I was expecting the long wait and figured I would be able to give these to some people as gifts. No... I won't be doing that.

Here are the problems that I have with these: the plastic bags on these are stuck under the top pieces and will take a lot of work to get them out, they do not line up very well when being closed, all 4 of the ones that I bought have little scratches on the mirrors and fingerprints all over them, they are dirty (which might have come from the fact that they were not sealed very well in the shipping bag and that came open on the long trip), you DO NOT get a very good variety, and the "gems" do not look very nice and are not inserted straight. I purchased 4 and only got red ones which was rather disappointing but not too surprising. Two of the designs were the same which makes sense when they only show a total of 3 designs. However, I didn't even get 1 of the designs that are shown and instead got a design that wasn't even in the picture.

Another thing to mention is that the colors of the stones for the ones in the pictures are not the same as the ones that I got. That's not that big of a deal to me, but if you are looking at these for the specific stone colors... don't expect them to be the same.

Overall, if the stones had been lined up in their spots and the mirrors not scratched, I probably could have dealt with the rest of the problems OK. I don't mind having to clean them although these are very difficult to clean since the top piece is raised so high from the red under it. The smell of the metal is very strong as well so hopefully cleaning it will get rid of that or dull it down. These did not come with any covers or bags, either, like others that I have purchased so if you are going to be putting it into a purse be prepared for the stones to come out and/or scratches on the outside. Personally, I'll be passing on these in the future for other ones that I have bought.

It's dark grey in color and is pretty thick.You don't have to apply a lot to cover your face. I applied the sea mud on my face and left it on for 15 minutes. By the way, you may want to warn people around you that you have this on so you don't scare them.. lol... While drying I felt a cooling sensation on my face which I found was pleasant. After 15 minutes passed, I used a facial buff with warm water and used circular patterns to clean the sea mud off and patted my face dry with a towel. The skin on my face felt clean, tighter, and had a nice glow to it. Overall I really like the sea mud. Next time I'm going to use it on my husbands face and see how he likes it.

column6: Retseliney Best Acne Face Mask & Oil Control, Organic Acne Treatment + 2% Salicylic Acid & Glycolic for Teens, Adult & Hormonal Acne, Clear Blemishes & Acne Scars, Helps Prevent New Breakouts
column14:
[[VIDEOID:d16f03ab949a35f0aa937c2aa85713f3]] Sadly, I still suffer from breakouts once or twice a month that drive me insane even though I follow a twice-daily skin care routine. This oil control face mask from Retseliney has been a gentle and effective way to keep my acne and blackheads under control!

I've tried mud masks and clay masks in the past, which always dry and make me feel like a living statue. This mask is thick, somewhat sticky and dries flexible! It's great to not have to worry about smiling with my face mask on and cracking it, or feeling like I can't make any expression without dealing with flakes of mask. I found that a thin layer worked best for me and it's very easy to get an even layer of product on my skin.

My face is very pale and can be very sensitive, especially to harsh products. This face mask is packed full of natural ingredients that treat my skin so well! The included juniper, cayenne and lavender are all organic and well-known for taking great care of skin. This mask also has green tea and aloe vera which make it wonderful for soothing irritated areas.

I've been very impressed with this mask from Retseliney, and I'm excited to add it - along with its cleanser and moisturizer counterparts from the same company - to my daily routines! I was provided with a sample of this mask but price doesn't change how great my skin feels after using it, nor does it effect my review.

column13: Eczema help is here! Also makes hands, cuticles & dry feet so soft!
column14:
I ordered this to help with my son's eczema and we've tried SO MANY products and dermatologist creams over the years. I'm tired of strong prescription strength creams that work a little but never make the eczema go away (and are expensive too!). I'm finding that this pure organic Argan Oil soothes his skin just as well and I feel better about the natural ingredients.

I like that the bottle had a plastic seal on it, and then it had a paper strip further securing it. The pump screwed on easily and makes it so much easier to use. My son can use it too, since he just turned 10 and I want him to start taking more care with his eczema care and preventing flare ups. I don't worry he will tip the bottle over and spill it all with an easy to use pump.

I am also using this for me as well, especially at night on my dry feet and it's making a big difference. I have problem acne areas from time to time on my chin too, and smoothing some on my chin since I read that it helps with acne. I have noticed that my cuticles are so soft now and my hands feel wonderful. I love that there is not a strong scent with this oil. My son HATES anything that has an odor of perfumes or smells "funny" and we can both use this product for many uses. I will continue to slather this oil in him 2-3 times a day over areas he has eczema. I see that the skin is not as red and it's so very helpful not to let his skin dry out. He scratches terribly at night when his skin gets dry, so this is a big part of our bedtime routine to calm his itching problems. Eczema is such a terrible ailment for so many children! I love trying new skin products so I was thrilled to receive this Argon Oil for free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. It's a quality product, and pure, Organic oil. I feel so good about buying the real deal oil, and not worry about harsh ingredients for me or my child.

column13: This product is not as terrible as people claim.
column14: Ok- I saw a headline on yahoo regarding how this sunscreen isn't great so I decided to post my review. I along with many bough this at Costco at half the price on amazon. My husband is Irish and fair skinned!! He burns walking in front of a window! So- I read the complaints this morning sent him a text on how he likes it and he said works good just greasy which sucks when you looked like you oiled up before you golf- but he said it's fine for the pool. We we at a water park for 4 hours in the Midwest when it was 97 degrees and the water even felt like a hot tub. My husband, 3 year old, and I lathered it on and never reapplied because we were too lazy and all that my husband got was a slight burn on the back of his shoulders. He's had way worse and we never reapplied. I see a lot of the photos of the sunburns and they are shoulder and back and I feel it comes down to lack of reapplication and not putting enough on. We used almost a whole tube of this just the 3 of us when we went and we are all slim people. You have to "liberally" apply and evenly. You should look like a greasy monster then your done. The greasy look goes away. Some people might not like that but it's an all natural sunscreen. I bought it because I checked out EWG skin deep website on sunscreen and SOOO many have high risk chemicals in them- so this might not be the most appealing but it works and unless your setting a timer on your watch and am having someone put it on your shoulders and back every 80min you really shouldnt diss this so bad. You can't put sunscreen on your back by yourself!! I like this stuff. I take my son to our local zoo several times a month and we lather in this and never get a burn. I have to put bronzer on my face just to look like I have color on it. You have be liberal about applying I mean a big glob just for your arm. I thinks it's one of the more affordable products on the market . I will continue to buy it.

column6: Tintocil Light Brown Cream Dye Brow Tint
column14: I am very impressed with this product for tinting brows. I have darkish red hair and my brows are more orange. This dye was a gradual change (it goes on white and darkens) but I kept it on until it was as dark as it was getting and am happy with the result. It seems like it can range from light to medium brown depending on how long you leave it. It doesn't have an orange tint as the packaging might imply. This stuff does not stain your skin. I was actually trying to stain mine to cover a small scar in my eyebrow. It washes off easily, which I realize is generally a good thing. The dye seems to last a long time. It has been a week and I haven't noticed any fading. Considering how long it seems to last and how little is needed to cover brows, this product is a really good deal compared to salon prices. Don't try to use it on your lashes unless you have help, your eyes need to remain closed or it will sting like you rubbed a chilli in your eyes.

column6: Philips Sonicare Essence Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column14: Bought this to replace a 5+ year old model that just wouldn't hold a charge anymore (it happens to all batteries eventually) and I still had 6 E-Series replacement heads. I admit that it is my own fault, I didn't read the description closely enough, but I am still very disappointed this model does NOT have the 30 second, quadrant timer feature. What really gets my goat is that Philips could have provided this important health feature with zero added expense, but deliberately chose not to. There is already a timer for 2 minute shut-off, this is a beeper/buzzer mechanism, I am 100% sure that all the  electronics are inside to provide the quadrant timer, and Philips went out of their way to disable it via their internal software, all so they could up-sell to a more profitable model. Yes, they are in business not to please customers but to make money, I understand this. Fine. But this is clearly a company that does not care about their customer's health, just the bottom line. In 18 months, after I've used up my supply of replacement heads, I'll be buying one of their competitor's models and will never buy another Philips product. I chose to buy from good companies, not sleazy ones.

column14: !!!Fake item!!! Bought this last week from the seller "Pharmapacks". I've been using the real Biosilk product for a while now and decided to buy it on amazon for cheaper. Shipping was fast. When it arrived, I examined both my previous authentic bottle and this new bottle and realized many differences. There were a lot more ingredients in fake product. Which caused a more alcoholic smell and made it more liquidy and more bubbly. It also contains both kinds of SLS which actually dries out hair. There were also many differences from the texts written on the bottles. The fake bottle does not have any register trademark symbols, which an authentic bottle should have after "Biosilk" and "Silk Therapy". I do NOT recommend buying this from Amazon. I recommend buying at a real salon even if it means paying more. It's worth the money. The original product is great!

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column14:
I used to be that person who could walk out the house, forget to put on deodorant, and be okay all day. For whatever reason, my body chemistry changed and I couldn't even go 10 minutes after a fresh shower without deodorant! Absolutely nothing worked for me in this Texas heat! I tried every extra strength, clinical protection, crystal deodorant on the market. Then I searched Amazon and found Green Tidings. I was a little thrown off by the price but I was willing to pay anything to combat the shame and embarrassment of walking around with my pits clinged closed, afraid to give anyone a hug or wave hello. I tried the 1oz sample lavender first. I loved it for its protection but the scent was too strong for my liking. Ecstatic over my results, I took the plunge and ordered the 3-pack unscented! This deodorant is absolutely amazing!!! I can go all day in 105 degree temps without reapplying and most importantly without having to do the sniff test throughout the day! I will gladly pay the price to walk around confidant in knowing that no one who passes me with get a whiff of onion-scented pits!
-Don's Wife

I'm a beginner when it comes to essential oils, but this tea tree oils seems to be your standard strength, and a good quality. The expiration date on the bottle I received is 07/2017, so it's good for two years.

column6: Shine Whitening - Zero Peroxide Teeth Whitening System - No Sensitivity
column13: The Shine Whitening-Zero Peroxide Teeth Whitening System works good
column14:
After using the Shine Whitening-Zero Peroxide Teeth Whitening System for 4 days my teeth have become slightly brighter. I didn't have any sensitivity to the product. As with teeth whitening systems that use peroxide this one is gentler on the gums and cheeks. It did take a couple days for my teeth to start showing any difference but it does. I drink a lot of Coke Zero with caffeine in it and I love fruit. So the stain on my teeth was hard to remove.

This product was easy to use. You boil some water in the microwave and place the mouth piece in the cup about 10 seconds. After that time the tray feels soft enough to place on your teeth to mold to your teeth. You take them out of your mouth and trim off the tab and rinse. You place a small amount of the whitening gel from the syringe in the trays on the side of your teeth that show when you smile. Do this on both trays. Place them in your mouth and insert the light resting them against your trays for 15 minutes twice a day. Remove them and rinse them.

You will like this product. It works well. This product arrived quickly and was packaged safely. I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review and all opinions are based on my personal experience with the Shine Whitening-Zero Peroxide Teeth Whitening System. column6: Hair Removal Wax Strips Legs + Body, 24 Count
column14: These hair removal wax strips for leg and body work well. I really like the design and that you don't have to heat the wax in a warmer or microwave. You aren't going to burn yourself with these strips as they don't require heating, only rubbing the strips in your hands to warm them. No actual heat source required. This pack comes with 24 strips, 12 (2 strips stuck together) and 2 wax cleansing cloths. Its best to let your hair grow a little to achieve the best results. They recommend the hair length to be at least 1/4 of an inch. These strips have a mild smell to them, but the smell does go away fairly quickly. The strips themselves work pretty well. I followed the directions and warmed the strips between my hands and then pulled them apart. I place both strips on my leg and rubbed several times in the direction of the hair growth. When it was time to pull the strips off, I was a little scared. I held the skin taut an and then ripped the strip off quickly. I'm not gonna lie, I screamed! It hurt but the pain went away fairly quickly. When I looked at the wax strip it had quite a bit of hair on it, My leg also looked pretty good. It did leave some hairs behind but not many. I continued to scream after each and every strip I ripped off and when I finished, my legs felt good. There were a couple spots I felt I needed to follow up with a razor to get remaining hairs but it really wasn't a lot. So far its been 3 days since I waxed using these strips and my legs still feel pretty good. I'm not sure if the hair will be gone for 8 weeks, or even a week for that matter but the longer the hair stays away the more likely I will be to purchase again. Overall so far so good. I purchase this product during a promotion at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Cremo Shave Cream, Astonishingly Superior Shaving Cream for Men
column13: Poor at first, OK after adjusting to difference; but, not on par with the best
column14: I have very sensitive skin and bought this based on the "Astonishingly" high claims and very good reviews. I have to optimize all the variables in my shave to get a comfortable BBS shave. Even so I get irritation issues too often. My skin tells me how I have done very clearly each and every shave.  At first I got several poor shaves with this. I gave it a 1 star review and now am revising it out of fairness due to the latest results. The trick was to maximize the slickness with a uniform addition of water, using a small brush (my fingers did not do a good and uniform job of mixing water into the face bound cream).  Now, I get good shaves this way, although not quite up to the level I get with the majority of tallow based soap/cream products available. It seems to be in the range with the good quality vegan (tallow/animal free) products out there. Not bad at all; but, not "Astonishingly" great either. It is weird, shaving with such a low visibility and thin product. There is no so called foam cushion effect with this.  An extra star off (3 to 2) for the over hyped advertisement. This product should work real well for most shavers as long as the hydrating issue is well done and they adapt to the lack of foam..

column6: Elizabeth Arden White Glove Skincare Fortifying Capsules, 37 Capsules
column13: Product feels good on skin, but I'm not sure what I received was fresh
column14:
I've used this product for the last 4 nights (it's a bit heavy to use during the day). While that may not be enough time to see great results, I can say that the product goes on feeling very silky--a feeling that is still there the next morning. For a very dry face like mine, waking up soft and silky is very preferable to waking up tight and dry. I think I will like this product even more the longer I use it. Also, the little pods the product comes in are cute, easy to use, and ensure you are using the correct amount of product. They would also be handy when traveling because they would cut down on the number of bottles I would have to pack.

The reason I gave this product 4 stars rather than 5 is not really a reflection on the product itself but on the seller. I looked it up online to be sure, but as soon as I squirted the first bit of product out of the little pod, I had a feeling I hadn't received a fresh product. While the picture of the product I found showed the serum to be a light beige-ish color, the product I received squirted out as a dijon mustard sort or color. It even had some swirls of brown as I squirted out the last of the pod. I was actually afraid to use the product at first, but since I received the product in exchange for an honest review, I took the chance and used it. Luckily, I've had no adverse affects from using the product as of yet. I do realize that some skin care products have longer shelf-lives than consumers realize, but discoloration is not a good sign and I was disappointed that I received the product in that condition. Had I paid the full price for the product, I would have been very upset and asked for a refund.

Elizabeth Arden is a name I trust my skin to, but I'm not sure I feel as trusting of this seller. The likelihood of me ordering from this seller again is not very high, unless it is a product that doesn't expire.

column13: I read all of the wonderful reviews so I figured I didn't have much to ...
column14:
I did not purchase on Amazon because I did not want to wait for delivery. My face has seemed uneven in tone lately, blotchy, and was breaking out. The skin was getting dry and I had picked at it and caused scabs. I do not get severe acne but from time to time my face will get pimples and clogged pours. I read all of the wonderful reviews so I figured I didn't have much to lose.

I used organic apple cider vinegar with it and left it on my face for 20 minutes. It was a bit tricky to get off because you don't want to clog your drains with the mask. With warm water and paper towels it did come off in time.

After I removed the mask I took a shower to wash any left over mask off. My skin was red after removing the mask but this disappeared after several minutes.

After my shower I noticed an immediate difference in my skin. The blotchiness disappeared. My skin felt tighter and more clean and the pores appeared less visible. The scab I had on my face became so small as the mask removed all of the dead dry skin around it. I truly saw a difference after one application. I cannot wait to use this again! Definitely recommend.

column6: Gillette Venus Embrace Women's Razor Blade Refills, Womens Razors / Blades
column14:
Great razor cartridges. My roommate and I both have slightly different Venus razors and these razor cartridges fit both of them perfectly.

The built in moisture ribbon isn't a substitute for shaving cream so you still need some type lubricant in my opinion, but it definitely contributes to a smoother shave. However, I think the key to these cartridges is the 5 blades. MY LEGS FEEL LIKE DOLPHINS AND MY ARM PITS HAVE NO INGROWN HAIRS!!! Sold. Once you start using 5 blades it's so hard to go back. I used a Gillette 3-blade razor when I was traveling last week and I wanted to shoot myself. Okay not really but I did finish my shower in a bad mood. It took forever compared to these ones! Seriously, upgrade and you'll thank yourself and each one of the 5 blades.

Also this pack is a great price for how long these last. Even though they are a little more than Gillette's 3- and 4-blade razor cartridges, they last noticeably longer. By the way, I don't really do this anymore because these blades last awhile, but if you're on a tight budget and really need your blades to last, you can keep a small cup of mineral/baby oil in your shower and soak your razor in it in between shaves. It keeps the blades sharp (mostly by staving off rust), but the only downside is it can start to dissolve the moisture strip.

Anyway, very happy with these! I'll definitely purchase again.

column6: Nautica Voyage Toilette Spray for Men
column13: It smelled awful. Like someone let a bottle of Windex ferment on a hot beach for a few weeks
column14:
Short answer: It smells awful. Do not buy it.

Long answer: Colognes are personal. They interact with your personal body chemistry and will smell differently for different people and at different times. Where you spray it (side of neck, chest, on clothes, on skin), how much you put on (one spray or 3), when you put it on (after a shower in the morning, after working out, before going out at night). All of these factors will influence how it smells. Not to mention the chance you receive a knock off as opposed to the real product.

So, that being said, Nautica Voyage for men did not smell good on me. It did not smell ok on me. It smelled awful. Like someone let a bottle of Windex ferment on a hot beach for a few weeks. Maybe it was me. Maybe it was one of those scents that do not work well with me. Maybe. All I know is that it was unusable. I tried. Really I did. I used it at different times, on different parts of my body and with varying amounts. Nothing helped. It still smelled like gasoline with chemical "beach smell" added in.

I ended up contacting the Amazon support center and explaining the situation. They were awesome. Refunded my order and sent me another one (I explained that it may have been a knockoff). However, it smelled the same, which it to say like garbage. I wish it were somewhat tolerable since the price is so great. I really could use a nice, causal, summer cologne. Well, live and learn.

column13: Where have these been all my life!?!
column14: These are the pins I've always searched for.  I have very thick long hip length hair that is coarse.  I've always preferred wearing my hair up in buns, especially at work.  While I was in the military, this hairstyle was required.  I've always had an extremely hard time finding pins that could keep my hair up and in place, especially during a lot of movement, as I was expected to run and do physical activities with my hair up.  I've went through so many pins over the years that only lasted a few weeks, if not days.  They'd bend while putting them in, or come out the bun distorted.  Some would even pop out on their own during the day.  Most could not hold my hair up, or in place.  I came across these pins during a search for hair accessories and didn't try them out because I was convinced I needed black hairpins to match my hair color.  I finally decided to purchase these after coming home from work the other day to find my bun out of place and a few pins missing from my hair.  I normally would use 10-12 of the Goody or Scunci brand hairpins and they would warp within the first couple of uses.  With these pins, I use 10, but think I could use as few as 8 if I wanted.  They slide in smoothly and hold extremely well.  My bun feels so secure during the day; there's absolutely no movement or slippage.  When I take them out at the end of the day, they come out looking the exact way as they were put in.  There's no warping or bending of the metal.  Because they slide in so well, they are completely hidden once put into place, so the fact that these are silver in color is of no consequence.  I absolutely love these hairpins!  My only regret is not getting them sooner, or when I was in the military, because these could've saved me so much time!  I highly recommend these if you have thick, long, coarse, or dark hair.  These are excellently made and will last a very long time.

column14: for those looking for an easy way to clean hummingbird feeders, The best way that I have found and it works great is by taking a hand full of rock salt (i.e  ice cream maker rock salt, or salt used for a water softner) and putting it into the feeder and adding just a few drops of warm water, shake the feeder making sure the salt swirls around all areas of the inside of  the feeder, then empty out the salt rinse with warm water, and there you go good as new. No fancy brushes needed. Hope this helps! BTW I love the larger feeder and my hummers are happy all summer long!!

column14: I have 4c grade hair and purchased this product to help with transitioning to natural hair after using chemical hair relaxers for many years. I'm hoping that I am a rare case. My decision to stop using relaxers was made because over the past 6 months I've been experiencing extreme hair thinning. I used this item 2 days ago in the shower, leaving it in for about 10 minutes while I showered. I experienced SO much hair fall, it was unbelievable and very stressful. I literally was pulling handfuls of strands of hair out. This is Day 2, and I'm still losing hair like crazy. Literally pulling it out. Hoping this will stop. It's  very stressful. I've never had anything like this happen before. It was also very drying for my hair and even contributed to knotting. I'll update if the hair fall stops.

column6: NHI Metallic Temporary Tattoos, 150+ Flash Tattoos Gold Silver, 8 Sheets - Aztec Tattoo, Mandala Tattoo, Mehndi Tattoo, Boho Temp Tattoo
column13: Fun, Awesome, Eye-Catching Metallic Temporary Tattoos
column14:
These Metallic Temporary Tattoos are pretty awesome! I'm highly impressed with them. These are perfect for the summer time. I haven't really found anything wrong with these Temporary Tattoos. Well at least nothing that sticks out to me. The colors are very shiny after you put them on. My favorite out of the 8 sheets were the sun and moon one.

Applying them is as easy as 1 2 3. It's just like putting on those temporary tattoos you used to get when you were a child. I find that the tattoos last a lot longer when you clean your skin first before applying the tattoo. They usually last for about a week or so.

How to apply:
1. Clean the area of the skin well.
2. Find the tattoo you want. Cut it out and peel off the plastic protector sheet.
3. Place the tattoo facing down and in the position you want.
4. Place a damp, warm rag or sponge on top of the tattoo and firmly hold it for about 30 seconds.
5. Remove the rag or sponge and slowly and gently remove the wet paper away from your skin.
6. Let the tattoo dry for about 2-3 minutes before touching it.
7. Now go out and show off your new tattoo!!

To remove:
Taking them off is very easy too. Just use a little bit of baby oil and rub gently and viola! The tattoos come off.

My daughter, little cousins, brother and nephew was ecstatic to see that I got these. My daughter already has put claim on some of the tattoos. And my little brother and nephew took more of the boy looking ones and used those. They absolutely love these tattoos.

Overall, I thought these are some fun, awesome, eye-catching tattoos. They are shiny and you're sure to stand out in the crowd. I'd recommend these for sure.

column14: My hair is between 2c/3a curl-wise and tends to frizz without a product to tame it.  I generally uses Pantene's curl gel but after seeing a review of Miss Jessie's I gave it a go and I'm totally in love.  Pantene tends to leave a bit of crunch in the curl if I'm not obsessive about towel drying the curls.  When I first tried Miss Jessie's I was exhausted so I just slapped some in my wet hair and went straight to bed. I woke up with absolutely perfect curls, with no crunch! Thinking this had to be a fluke I tried the product again and went through the whole towel dry rigmarole and was even happier with the way they came out. Loads of volume, perfect big spirals.  There was some leftover frizz from the friction of towel drying but a bit of B&B invisible oil fixed that.  This is really an amazing product. It doesn't weigh my curls down at all, it's scentless, it doesn't leave a residue or cake the curls together creating Medusa-like crunchy curls.  I just wound up with soft shiny spirals. So happy with this product, and at such a low price I'm totally going to stock up!

column6: Simple Kind to Skin Cleansing Water, Micellar 6.7 oz
column13: almost too good to be true
column14: I started looking for micellar water and after seeing a post on a beauty blog about how it's the best, easiest cleanser you can use, and all of the French women use it and have fantastic skin. I couldn't find any of my local stores so I turned Amazon and voilà there it was, ranging  in price from approximately five dollars a bottle up to $20-$30 a bottle. I'm fairly frugal so I went low-end and bought the simple water and after using it for a month I am very pleased with it. I simply saturate some flat cotton  pads with the micellar water and rub the pads across my face, and all my make up is removed. I don't wear a ton of make up, but I do wear bareMinerals powder foundation, and Christian Dior mascara. Both products came off very easily with the micellar water. It feels like tapwater; there's no fragrance to it and it doesn't foam up which took some getting used to, but it gets my face 90% clean, and I use it which is the best part of all. I'm one of those lazy gals that will sleep in my make up more often than not, but this stuff is so easy and effective that it was easy to work into my routine. Finding it in a three pack made it easy for me to stock up; if only it were available on Subscribe  and Save - then it would be perfect. Give it a try, you won't be sorry you did.

We are lucky enough to have our own pool at home. But owning a pool also comes the flow of several kids in and out of your pool daily! I also have a 12 month and and have an in home daycare. So sunscreen is a must around my house and we use large amounts of it! I am always cautious of the brands I choose, and the SPF for my children, especially my infant. I started using Tender Sprout Organic Sunblock this weekend and I am very please with how affective the product is. In the past I have used products and they caused my babies eyes to become read, runny, and irritated. Which in turn causes him to be super grouchy and uncomfortable. So I would try to apply less in those sensitive areas to only have him burn. With the Tender Sprouts Organic sunscreen i am able to apply it generously to his face and ear area, and he has no bad effects from it! It hasn't burnt his eyes, or left him with irritated in any area. It also kept him from being sunburnt, which to me is the best part! He was in the water for several hours, and I didn't have to reapply it any and it protected him all day. I feel so good about
using the Tender Sprouts Organic sunscreen because I know there are no harsh chemicals in it, and it protects my children from the harmful rays of sun. I love the fact that this product provides chemical free, fragrance free protection for my child and I will be using more of this product in the future, because it's proven to be a company I can trust! I received this product at a discount price in exchange fore my honest, unbiased review. The price has nothing to do with my opinion of the product.

column6: Pure Vitamin E -JOJOBA OIL - Richer than Vitamin E Oil - Best stretch mark oil - 100% Pure, Organic Cold Pressed, Unrefined - PREMIUM Quality - Oil For Hair, Skin, Face, Acne, Lips, Cuticles, Beard - Anti-Aging - Made in USA - Money Back Guarantee - Limited Quantity
column14:
Before buying this Jojoba Oil I had heard all of the benefits of using it. The main reason I decided to give it a try was for my poor hair! My hair is very thin and very greasy. Because my hair becomes greasy very quickly and easily after washing it I have to sacrafice conditioner as it tends to leave my hair even more greasy. Not being able to use conditioner leaves my hair very dry and to make matters worse I straighten it close to 6 times a week and my scalp because very itch due to the dryness.

The first thing I did once I ripped open my jojoba oil was wash my hair then apply this to my scalp and working my way down to my roots. I was so amazed at how well my hair reacted to the jojoba oil. I didn't expect it to do anything other than make my hair more oily but surprisingly it calmed my itchy scalp, moisturized my dry strands and didn't leave my hair oily like conditioner!

I also noticed that jojoba could be used to help with razor burn and since I already had it I figured why not. Now I get razor burn each time I shave, I know lucky me. I have tried tea tree oil with no success and again I really didn't expect the jojoba oil to do much. I did have to apply it a few times over the course of the hour before swimming but it really helped to reduce the razor burn. Even if it didn't help with the razor but my skin sure loved the smooth feeling it left! Such a great multi use oil! *I received this product free/discounted in exchange for my review. My reviews are completely honest and 100% my own.*

column13: Exceptional results for those with realistic expecations
column14: This is by far the best serum I have ever used.  The results were noticeable after about 30 days (using as directed morning and night). I have seen a slight reduction in the vertical lines between my eyebrows and the "crows feet" at the corners of my eyes as well as an overall improvement in the texture of the my skin.  Please note:  I have very realistic expectations.  I am 55 years old and I do not want or expect my skin to look like I am 40. The consistency is different from other serums as it is liquid and not creamy.  That is a plus for me because when followed (as directed) by eye cream and a moisturizer, other serums cause too much oiliness.  The bottom line:  this a an excellent product and a GREAT value if you have realistic expectations about what to expect from any beauty treatment.

column6: Gold Bond Rough & Bumpy Daily Skin Therapy, 8 Ounce Pack of 3
column14:
Okay, not too many things you'll hear me say this about, what with me being a rationalist and all, but this stuff is MAGIC!

I almost didn't write this review, because I'm only going to repeat what so many others have said, but turns out, I am so amazed I can't stifle myself, so here goes:

Among other charmingnesses that I've noticed since ('scuse me for getting personal here, but) menopause arrived, is that my skin is going wacko. The relevant example here is that after years of accepting smooth skin as only natural, all of a sudden my forearms turned into something akin to those spiky things put up to discourage drivers from escaping police during chases, or driving the wrong way out of parking garages.

I don't know why, out of all the changes, this is the one that bugged me, but it did-- enough to look online to try to figure out what was up with it. I succeeded, and discovered it's something called keratosis pilosis, or KP for short (why something so unendearing earns a nickname is beyond me; I'd prefer to call it yukskin, but that's just me, I guess).

The reason I'm going into such detail is so that if any of you out there have the same thing and are wondering if this might succeed in returning your skin to its former state, you'll know that my experience might be relevant, and the answer is a great big glorious YES!

I could feel a change from-- get this-- the first application.

Mind you, it didn't make the bumps vanish at that point...but it did make them, for lack of a better description, less spiky.

It seemed to me that, day by day, they were gradually and consistently improving, but I didn't trust this impression, chalking it up to wishful thinking...or maybe to having been brainwashed by having read the other reviews here.

Well, it's been three weeks, and there's no longer any arguing with the results: although my skin is not as it was pre-menopause, in that there are still bumps, they are much smaller, and there is zero spikiness (meaning, the bumps are now neither hard nor sharp).

And even this is not totally accurate, because-- how odd is this?-- it's actually only my right arm that still has any bumps at all. My left really is just smooth, which I'm hoping might be a harbinger of things to come for the laggard arm.

Since I am continuing, still, after three weeks, to see improvement as I daily apply this stuff, my guess would be that eventually both arms will be as they were in their days of glory (okay, after all this, I have to admit, I don't really care all that much about the state of my arms, and probably wouldn't have even noticed it but for the fact that I evidently have a habit of rubbing my arms while driving and stopped at lights, for want, I guess, of anything more edifying to do (I refuse to be one of those people who uses their phone or tablet behind the wheel, don't get me started), and was, one day, suddenly shocked to discover this whole armSpikes thing out of nowhere).

So, while I obviously can't guarantee that anyone else will have the same happy experience I've had with this product, I would certainly say it's worth giving it a shot if you, like me, grew tired of risking hand injury while rubbing your arm (or whatever), because I swear, it worked like magic for me.

Further affiant sayeth naught.

column13: Fantastic sunscreen for both adults and children!
column14:
As a three time melanoma survivor, I was happy to receive this sunscreen as a product review. I also have four tween age daughters (ages 9, 10, 11 and 13) who are very active and we go through a great deal of sunscreen in our house. I have taken my time to really put this sunscreen to the test and I love it and highly recommend it! This is what I found:
Pros: Is it effective? YES! I put this lotion to the test in various situations. At the pool, beach, gardening, boating, zoo trip, etc. It was effective in every situation, even if not reapplied after a few hours. (I always reapply but getting Tweens to do so is not easy.)
Is it easy to apply? Absolutely! I tend to use spray sunscreen because of how quick and easy they are to use with a busy schedule and multiple children. Many lotions tend to be thick and hard to apply. NOT this sunscreen. It has a great consistency, not too thick or thin and rubs in with ease! My busy kids were even able to apply it without help! And a bonus is that it has a nice, very light scent.
Is it good for sensitive skin? YES! This was a major pro for us. Two of my daughters have extremely sensitive skin and easily have rashes/breakouts from other sunscreens. Both girls had no problems at all with this lotion. In fact, it is now their lotion of choice and the only one they want to use!

Cons-The only con I have is the price. This is priced higher than the sunscreen we tend to buy at the drugstore. I was skeptical that I would actually rebuy after my review bottle was gone. However, I discovered that this tube lasts MUCH longer than our normal sunscreen. I was surprised at the number of applications we got out of one tube. I will definitely be buying more in our future. It has become over favorite sunscreen!

The good: their a faint smell, that dissipates quickly (not at all a problem), and while it's heavy, I have found it absorbs well without being sticky (even in the midst of a humid summer). It is a good lotion.

column14:
My husband loves the scent and I've found that the scent isn't too masculine or strong to be used by a woman.

column6: Maybelline New York Shine Free - Loose Oil Control Loose Powder, 0.7 Ounce
column14:
Great stuff. Though I admit I often forget this step, I know it's super important to use some type of setting powder (or spray) whenever you use liquid or cream foundation to help keep it in place and stave off oily shine. When I recently ran out of the bareminerals mineral veil I've always used in the past, a friend recommended this stuff from Maybelline, and WOW! I seriously have no reason to go back to bareminerals. This stuff from Maybelline works just the same, is 1/3rd the price, and comes in a bigger container.

A few things I want to note:
1) this comes with an application puff that fits inside the container. While this is nice to have, I get much more even results using a brush. I just feel like a brush is better at spreading a thin layer of this stuff evenly without disturbing your not-quite-dry liquid or cream foundation underneath. The easiest way to do this is to just tap some of the product into the blue cap, swirl it with the brush, and apply.
2) This has very little color to it (which is what most people want in a setting powder, but just in case..). Even though it looks like any powder foundation when it's in the container, it's very, very fine so it's not going to cover your imperfections like a foundation would. However, it can definitely be used by itself if you have particularly oily skin and just want to keep the shine at bay. And on that note, if you're using this as a setting powder over your liquid or cream foundation, you don't have to worry too much about this being an exact color match since it's almost translucent when using a very thin layer.

column6: Colgate Max White Full Head Toothbrush (Pack of 6)
column13: POOR DESIGN PLUS BRISTLES SOFTEN TOO QUICKLY AND BECOME INEFFECTIVE
column14: Being a hygienist I've found this toothbrush to be totally inadequate; seeing that others feel this brush isn't "aging" gives me even more reason to dislike the manual Max White brush. Why? Because the bristles become way too soft and ineffective after only a few weeks of use. They might look fine, but my teeth aren't clean after brushing. My thought was that those who aren't as aware of how their teeth should feel might not realize that they aren't performing adequate hygiene. And some reviews here seem to reflect this. Luckily, there were quite a few brushes in the package I purchased so each brush gets its few weeks then is tossed in the trash. Also, the outer bristles are too long and the flatter middle bristles don't quite contact the flatter tooth surfaces. In order cleanse all surfaces it's sometimes necessary to push down harder on the longer bristles which could create damage to the sulcus (shallow "collar" around the tooth) in time.

column6: RioRand Multifunction Electric Facial & Body Brush Spa Cleaning System (4 in 1 Blue)
column13: No more or less than what I was expecting
column14: So far I'm impressed with this inexpensive little facial cleansing brush. The case is nice and sturdy. The brush attachment is soft and gentle, yet effective. The massage attachment (one with 4 rolling balls) felt very nice when used with my nourishing mask. Although the balls are hard plastic, they were surprisingly gentle. I have not yet tried the other two attachments, but I have inspected them and they look to be as sturdy and well made as the other two attachments.  The motorized handle is lightweight yet solid.  It has worked well so far and shows no signs of quitting any time soon.  While on high, it's quite a little work horse!  My skin feels completely exfoliated and new, however if I'm not careful and stop soon enough, I can go too far and cause agitation. So it is certainly capable in high speed. In low speed it is gentle, yet effective in keeping pore clogging dead skin cells and gunk in check.  I will be honest, in low, it doesn't take much pressure to slow/bog it down. Personally, I'm not deterred by this. It serves as a reminder not to be too rough on my delicate skin. Plus, what else would you expect from a device that only requires 2 small batteries and costs less than $30??  Regardless, it certainly gets the job done in my opinion and I have no delusions of it working for years and years. If I get 4 to 6 months use out of this thing, I got my money's worth.  I am satisfied with my purchase and I got exactly what I was looking for in a product. For the price I paid, I feel I got a good deal too.  I've been using this for about two weeks and the batteries are still going strong with daily use.  If my opinion changes,  I will update this review.

column6: All Natural Coral Safe / Reef Safe / Biodegradable Sunscreen - SPF 30 - 8 fl Oz - Water Resistant and Coral Safe! Approved Snorkeling and Scuba Diving Sunscreen!
column13: Limited Use - Not Very Effective Outside of Water
column14:
I bought this product to go snorkeling in Cancun. It did seem to adhere to the skin pretty well. I even had trouble scrubbing it off my skin afterwards, in the shower. However outside of the water the product seemed useless, unless you want to walk around looking like a ghost. It seems it only blocks the sun if you apply it and leave it as a thick white paste. (I called it my "geisha" sunscreen.) I rubbed it a bit on my skin to avoid the ghost appearance, and my skin burned after walking around for a while. Then when you start to sweat, it would drip and run, and leave pink trails on your arms and legs.

So, perhaps it is good for the coral in the water. But bring another sunscreen when you are out of the water.

column6: Schick Intuition  Renewing Moisture Razor Blade Refills
column14:
I have very, very sensitive skin. If I scratch my arm, I will have nail marks from where I scratch. Because of this, shaving my legs often is an issue because they get very irritated. On top of that, I have a type of eczema that also makes it difficult.

I purchased the intuition razor previously and was still having issues. I came across the sensitive refills and decided that I really needed to try these as it could be my solution and I am SO happy I did.

Ever since using these refills, I am able to shave as often as I would like without having any adverse reactions. My legs are smooth and soft again.

My only downfall is that I feel like the bottom half of the razor always goes quicker than the top which makes me feel like I am wasting half of the razor towards the end. However, that is not nearly enough for me ton stray away from using these. Any one with sensitive skin should definitely look into these.

column14:
Ultra Moisture Magnet Serum 50X Hyaluronic Acid has a unique non-equilibrium gel structure with gel domains that bounds the water tightly. The formula creates a film on the layer of the skin and transports this water over time. The 50X Strength of the Hyaluronic Acid makes it more potent and provides maximum water binding capacity.

One single application of this HA makes the skin look a lot younger, radiant and even-toned. Using this moisturizer/serum the skin would be dramatically plumped and lifted with incredible moisture.
This Serum is GENTLE, EFFECTIVE & SAFE for all skin types; including those with sensitive skin.

Vegan, Paraben-free, oil-free, no dyes, no fragrances or fillers, Oily Skin remedy
- Rejuvenates the look of dull skin for a smoother, more even skin tone
- Helps in fighting with the dryness /redness on face with professional hydration
- Diminishes the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles
- Fights with the dark circles under the eyes and the eye puffiness

50x Strength Hyaluronic Acid can hold 4,000 to 5,000 times its own weight in water. As it binds water to it, the individual molecules expand. This inflation of the Serum on a molecular level helps to plump the skin. It hydrates the skin and reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles and gives you a healthy, plump, smooth and glowing appearance. The amazing plumping abilities of 50 x Strength Hyaluronic Acid can be demonstrated with a dried apricot. After a few hours' immersions in a beaker of the ingredient, a dried apricot will hydrate and plump back to its original shape and my wife totally swears by this product,
wrinkle removing and prevention that is too Frankenstein like for me but what ever it takes for the bride to keep from looking like broom Hilda I good with it.

column13: A little potent but worth it.
column14:
I started using this line of products a few months ago after reading several positive reviews. I'm 36 have always battled severe acne and discoloration. It's generally horrible. I started with just the serum, then added the cleanser, then the night cream, then the toner and then the mask.

Overall, this combination of products has drastically improved the look feel and overall health of my skin.

This serum is great, and I've noticed a drastic improvement in my skin since I started using it, but sometimes it does cause minor irritations like blotching, minor itching and a little dryness. I only use it at night because of this and I always follow up with the night cream. If you have sensitive skin like I do, I do not recommend using this serum more than once a day. I can say however, that there is a noticeable difference in my skins condition and appearance and I feel I look healthier than I ever have.

I now can wear less makeup and even feel comfortable wearing my hair out of my face on a regular basis. I've never felt better about my own face and it's because I decided to invest in a line of quality products that actually works for me. I have tried several other product lines on both the mainstream cosmetic side and the natural side resulting in poor or nightmarish results.

There's something about this line that just works for me and I'm so thankful. I may sound a little dramatic here but for me it's a big deal. Being able to actually like the skin on my face has been a big life changer for me. I recommend this line to anyone with combination and sensitive skin. It all takes a little getting used to but it's completely worth it.

column13: Good false lashes for adding volume and length
column14: I’m new to false lashes, but I have always wanted to try them.  I was given the opportunity to purchase the Iris in Paris Professional False Eyelashes set at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review so I took it.  The eyelash set is made of plastic and has a bit of sheen to it.  Looking at the lashes there is a distinct pattern as to how they were manufactured; two long lashes followed by about seven shorter lashes then two long lashes then about seven short.  That pattern continues for the entire lash.  I would have preferred a more random look to the lashes.  To apply the lashes you will need to peel them off the plastic based.  The application glue is included in the set and glue is applied to the back brim of the lashes using the wand included in the glue.  The glue should set for about 30 seconds and start to get tacky before you try to apply the lashes.  I had an incredibly difficult time getting the lashes to adhere to my eyelids.  The glue went from wet to dry and never really got tacky.  I was able to get the middle to stay attached; however both ends wouldn’t stay on.  For as well as I was able to wear them they felt good, I could tell they were there, but they weren’t bothering me. Outside of my application issues, which very well could be user error, I like the lashes.

column13: A fine deodorant, but tries a little too hard to oversell itself
column14: I got a free sample of Secret Outlast® Clear Gel thanks to Secret and even though I'm not a fan of gel deodorants, I gave it a whirl. When I first put it on, it was the goopy gel feeling that I knew and hated. I have to say that once it dried, you didn't feel any unpleasant wetness like most gel deodorants. As usual though, the product is a mess when applying - pushing gel through those tiny holes always end up with deodorant all over the place. It would be a much better product if it was dispensed as a gel solid, like Axe deodorant. The first say I wore  Secret Outlast® Clear Gel, it did a pretty good job of keeping me dry (even in 90 degree heat). That being said, it does not offer 48 hour protection like the advertising boasts (not that I think any deodorant really can) because I was a sweaty Betty by the next morning. Also, it still left white streaks on my shirt so I will not be converting in the future.

column6: Instanatural Vitamin C Toner
column14:
I started using this line of products a few months ago after reading several positive reviews. I'm 36 have always battled severe acne and discoloration. It's generally horrible. I started with just the serum, then added the cleanser, then the night cream, then the toner and then the mask.

Overall, this combination of products has drastically improved the look feel and overall health of my skin.

This toner has been great in balancing out my skins blotches and discolorations and works as a great prep for makeup application in the morning. It also feels just so refreshing to apply after cleansing too. It doesn't leave my skin feeling dry or stripped either which is a bonus.

I now can wear less makeup and even feel comfortable wearing my hair out of my face on a regular basis. I've never felt better about my own face and it's because I decided to invest in a line of quality products that actually works for me. I have tried several other product lines on both the mainstream cosmetic side and the natural side resulting in poor or nightmarish results.

There's something about this line that just works for me and I'm so thankful. I may sound a little dramatic here but for me it's a big deal. Being able to actually like the skin on my face has been a big life changer for me. I recommend this line to anyone with combination and sensitive skin. It all takes a little getting used to but it's completely worth it.

column6: Christian Dior Voluptuous Care Lipcolor, # 651 Tourbillion Pink, 0.12 Ounce
column14:
I have owned several Dior lipsticks before, including this color. Dior is always luxurious and never disappointing, but then I'm personally a Dior/Chanel/Burberry girl. I have sensitive skin and my lips get dry easily, so I can never use drugstore make-up. This lipstick doesn't cause any irritation or drying, I apply a lip balm over it, but it's not necessary as this is slightly moisturizing. The lipstick has a mild scent, it's not offensive, but it's not scent-free. Color is very natural and great for a casual-I'm-not-really-wearing-make-up look.

I received it in a pouch, not a box. The product is nice, but I'm a little surprised that the lipstick case looks scuffed up. The lipstick tube itself looks new and unused, but there are noticeable blemishes on the box including a crack on the front and a dent on the side and general scratches. This is how my lipstick should look after rolling around in my makeup bag for several months, which is a little disappointing - part of the Dior allure is the luxe feel of a brand new item. This is not a tester. Bottom line, if you wanted this lipstick for less than Dior ($5 less) get this, you won't be disappointed.

Disclaimer: I received this at a discount for my honest review. For the discounted price, it was worth it and I would buy it again. At full price, probably not.

column6: Volumizing Black Mascara - Mineral-Based, Gluten-Free, Vegan, Cruelty-Free, Paraben-Free Formula, Cate McNabb Cosmetics, 0.25 oz.
column14: Before I purchased this mascara, I checked it out with my eye surgeon - I have chronic dry eye syndrome and chronic Iritis, an inflammation of the iris. She doesn't advise daily eye makeup for me, but after I gave her the specs on this product ( mineral formula, vegan and non waterproof ) she gave me the go-ahead for occasional use. Yipee! Special occasions just became more special! The product packaging is beautiful, and looks like a very high end, very expensive department store mascara. It applies very smoothly, with no clumping or flaking. The color is very black, which I love, and really makes even the tiniest lashes really pop. I experienced zero irritation with this mascara, and it washed off easily and cleanly with mild soap and water. Several reviewers thought that it was a little expensive, but I thought it was well priced. Frankly, I would pay more just for the ability to wear mascara again! I purchased this awesome mascara at a discounted price for an honest review.

column6: Dragonhawk Complete Tattoo Kit 3 Pro Machines Gun Immortal Inks Power Supply Tattoo Needles Tips Grips 3-2YMX
column13: so I bought this gun for fun and to make some extra money
column14:
I have no desire to become a professional tattoo artist, however I am a college student with a talent for drawing and a knack for getting into trouble, so I bought this gun for fun and to make some extra money. I did not expect this to be a professional gun and had little hopes for it. That being said I DID rate it 4 stars. Mainly because this was the best option I found on Amazon. I generally recommend it.

Problems: First, don't use the inks. I bought two six ounce bottles of GOOD ink for 14 bucks, they're worth the invest if you hope the tattoos you're giving are any good. Second, there are no instructions as to how you should go about setting up the gun. I'm pretty sure most of these parts are unnecessary, or extra, and I have no idea what to do with all these damn rubber bands. I suppose I'll figure it out when the thing starts falling apart. There's also no return address, which I find particularly shady. And there are only 5 needles.

Despite all the issues, it came within three days of me ordering it, and I'm still waiting on the ink. If anyone knows how to put this thing together, please contact me.

column13: I really like Hyaluronic Acid products but not this one...
column14:
The irony of this for me is I was super excited to try this product. I received a coupon so I was getting it at a reduced rate and was excited to try a '50x Strength Hyaluronic Acid' product, it has been awhile since I used anything with HA and I thought it was going to be a nice addition to the glycolic acid and rosehip oil face treatments I'm currently using to lessen the brown spots/melasma. My review will not be favorable but it will be truthful.

This product smells terrible. I know smells are subjective but I do see other reviews of this product that mention the smell and all I can say is they are understating the problem.

NOTE: the packaging for this container is pretty 'home kitchen' looking. They use a clear back plastic label on the bottle that isn't centered evenly on the bottle and the plain white box for the product also has a clear/black printed sticker for identification. This product is just not very professional and the texture of the product, while it does have a gel-like that is to be expected of HA, it is also watery at the same time and slides right off the back of your hand.

I do like the design of the container and I didn't feel any adverse skin issues after the 3 times that I did use it so I'm giving it 2 stars but the smell is enough to keep me from using it again so if it does perform well, I'll never know.

column6: No! No! Hair Removal Device
column13: Product has manufacturing issues --not reliable at all
column14:
I gave this product more than a fair chance by getting THREE over a span of 18 months. My first No No worked beatifully on my legs and upper lip. It took just a few weeks to stop hair growth for several months, but when I returned to use my No No had stopped working. I bought a second one that never worked after a few weeks and never removed hair as well as the first. So I resumed use of a depilatory for a year before ordering yet a third No No hoping the issues had been resolved. To say I was disappointed is all that is necessary
The product is VERY inconsistent and unreliable --even after a recharge. If you are lucky enough to get one that works, you will have great results but will be disappointed when it no longer works when hair . eventually returns. Don't be surprised if it does not work at all at the first use; if that happens return for a refund because it will not improve.

I am beyond happy with this product! I recently lost a very close friend and the stress and shock of it has caused my hair to break and fall out. I have fine and thin hair to begin with. So I was desperate to find something that would help. I have been using this for about a week now, and I couldn't be happier! My hair is like silk. And I have noticed a lot less hair in the drain and brush. That means more hair on my head, yay!

This product is very creamy, and a little goes a long way. Which is great considering the price. But this product has saved my hair, making it's value way higher then what I paid. I will definitely be using this product from now on. Not to mention, this is one of the best prices I have found for this shampoo. I also saw a couple of reviews saying that this isn't the real product. As soon as I got it (and the conditioner) I took it to my stylist. She has used the product many, many times. She is very familiar with what it's supposed to look like, smell like, and feel like. She confirmed that this and the conditioner I bought ( Kerastase Resistance Ciment Anti-Usure Conditioner, 6.8 oz Sold by: Beauty Aid Essentials) were the genuine product. I believe this seller is trust worthy, and I will continue to get these products from them! Thanks so much! :)
