column6: Virilem - Nail Clipper Set - Fingernail And Toenail Clippers
column14:
Six months ago I reviewed the Virilem Fingernail clipper, and I couldn’t hide my enthusiasm:

“Nail clippers? Really? My immediate reaction when approached to review this product was a huh-moment. One would be hard pressed to find a junk drawer in America that doesn’t hold at least one dime store nail clipper. So I didn’t think there was anything a manufacturer could do to improve upon something so basic in male grooming. Wrong! These aren’t the same cute little chrome clippers; they’re turbo-charged. I’m talking strong, durable stainless steel, and precision sharp at the business end.

As a single guy, a million years ago, I learned that first impressions go a long way when meeting women. They are very detail oriented, and a man’s fingernails are a visual calling card that can be more impressive than a platinum bankcard. Virilem Nail Clippers are well made and very sharp - sharp enough to also do a great job on toenails. But clear the room, because those thick toenail clippings can be semi-dangerous projected missiles.

While this device looks like most other nail clippers, once you hold it in your hand, the difference is clear. It has the feel of a real tool. Virilem has designed and manufactured a high quality clipper that precisely cuts nails. But there’s more! The rounded edge of the clipper’s lever is perfect for pushing back cuticles to facilitate uniform nail growth. So it’s a complete nail grooming station in one little device. A lifetime or 30-day money back guarantee tells me that Virilem Nail Clippers For Men has set a new gold standard for the well-groomed male.”

Virilem has done it again! With the packaging a fingernail clipper and a toenail clipper, Virilem now offers a complete nail grooming solution. There are growing concerns about the sanitary conditions of some local nail salons. So I opted to do my own nails. This quality set simplifies the task for trimming both my fingernails and toenails. Highly recommended! A sample product was provided for this unbiased review.toenails. Highly recommended! A sample product was provided for this unbiased review.

column6: InstaNatural Hyaluronic Acid Serum - Anti Aging Serum for Face - Reduces Wrinkles, Fine Lines & More - For Youthful & Radiant Skin - With Vitamin C Serum and More - 2 OZ
column13: Not a miracle wrinkle treatment, but I've had positive results so far.
column14:
I have to admit I didn't have high expectations. If you're looking for a miracle wrinkle buster, this is not it. However, I've been using this on my face, neck, and chest for about two weeks and I'm seeing positive change! I'm very fair and subject to autoimmune rashes on my face. Also, I have a very pronounced T-Zone where my face is oily on/around my nose, up and across my forehead, but dry everywhere else.

My skin is smoother and this serum is evening out my skin tone. My face is definitely firmer. My T-Zone is noticeably less oily and my dry zone is noticeably less dry. I love that I can rub it on my eyelids and it doesn't sting or otherwise affect my eyes, which are very sensitive. It will take a long time for me to know for sure if this protects me from the environmental impacts that age our skin. However, I like it enough that I plan to keep using it.

I suggest you Google Hyaluronic Acid and read about it's uses. Apparently it is medically a good and positive substance, and I couldn't find any negative side affects. There is interesting information out there. It is used in eye surgery and to treat arthritis among other things.

column6: Zennery LED Fogless Lighted Shower Mirror with Accessory Holder - Waterproof
column13: No more 'touch ups' needed after my shower! Fantastic Customer Service!
column14: Update of my update 8-28-15: I contacted the seller directly about the light malfunction (and possible manufacturing issue) mine was having and received a swift response, apology of the issue, thanked me for my detailed pictures and would like to send me a replacement at no charge!   I just received it today and cant wait to put it to use!  Update 8-18-2015: Sadly I must decrease my rating in half as my mirror light has already met its demise.  First it just wouldn't light at all, then they stayed on constantly at about 1/10 power.  Thinking that possibly it had been accidentally left on all day, I changed out the batteries with no change.  Then I noticed the entire window housing the led's was full of water.  Upon taking a closer look I see that the portion of the housing for this light assembly that faces up was not sealed at all but the bottom side that water could have attempted to get out was sealed up tight.  Perhaps mine was a manufacturing defect?  The batteries seem sealed up very well....  For me, this light feature is worth half the value to me and without it, this is just another fog free mirror and definitely not worthy of the listed price.  Original Review: For years now I have been shaving in the shower.  It's better for your skin and mitigates the issue of nicks.  I shave my whole head several times a week so that's a whole lot of shave time going on.  I have gone through a few other types of shower mirrors in the past.  I always end up having to use fog-x, soap or routinely rinse it to keep it from fogging up on me.  This mirror solves that issue by the refillable reservoir that keeps it at the temperature of the water hence no fog.  I also like to keep just a low light on while showering but sometimes miss a patch or two and have to touch up areas after my shower.  The added led lighting is a great addition.  They touch sensor switch worked very well whether my hands were dry, wet, or even had shaving cream on them.  Just don't look down into the lights as they are pretty bright.  It would be nice if there were 2-3 levels of lights but they do work well.  I do like that it comes with 3 ways to attach it included.  The included squeegee is a nice addition (also with the built in storage for it). It would be nice at the standard price point for them to include the required batteries.  I have agreed to write this review in exchange for a discounted product.  This has not influenced my review or rating in any way.  So far this is a great product!

column6: JOICO Color Endure Violet Shampoo, 10.1 Ounce
column14:
I quite like this purple shampoo. I left it on for about 8 minutes and it toned most of the ugly golden tones out of my color treated blond hair. It's a very dark purple so it's a bit off-putting at first. But it spreads easily through the hair and I was able to work up a nice lather. It also left my hair clean, which isn't always the case with toning shampoos. And it didn't leave my hair dry and tangled, although I did follow it with a Pureology conditioner (really good btw) that is very hydrating. I think I probably could have left it on for a longer period of time, but I was hesitant because this was the first time I'd used it and you can never tell how strong a toning shampoo will be. It also smells really nice, more floral than chemical. The next time I use it, I think I'll leave it on a bit longer. I'm hoping that it will last through a regular shampooing so I won't have to use it every time. If it does, I'll update this review to five stars! It was a good buy and I think it's priced pretty fairly. It was much cheaper on Amazon than it was at Ulta. I'm tempted to purchase the Joico purple conditioner too. Maybe they'll work even better together! All in all, I'm pleased with my purchase and definitely recommend this shampoo for anyone struggling with unwanted golden tones in blond hair. It worked really well for me.

Update: The effects of this shampoo do not last through a regular shampoo. I quite like my regular products (Pureology Perfect 4 Platinum and Living Proof Perfect Hair Day) and the way they make my hair look and feel healthy. So rather than use this shampoo every time, I decided to try using a violet demi permanent toner. Redken Shades EQ is awesome and the shade 9V worked perfectly. It toned all of the ugly golden tones out of my hair, doing no damage and leaving my hair soft and glossy. I left it in for 5 minutes and it lasts about 15-20 shampoos. This is a much better solution for me than using a toning shampoo every time I wash my hair. I can use my regular products (which are sulfate free and therefore color safe) which is a very good thing. Using this toner was a very good decision and although I'll keep Color Endure on hand, I really don't need it very often. In fact, I only use it when I'm due for a refresh of the toner and simply haven't had time to get to do it. If you're tired of having to use this shampoo every time you wash your hair, then consider trying Shades EQ. It was a great decision for me.I wash my hair. Had been looking for a nice beard trimmer for some time and opted for this Philips Norelco model mostly based on the reviews I read and watched online. The laser on the trimmer has some value other than just being a freaking laser, yes it does move with the trimmer, but you can use it verify that you have straight lines.

I like the fact that the plastic guard is set in a fixed position depending on what setting you choose on the led display, as opposed to my old beard trimmer which had only a few settings, and was not fixed, which usually led to a disaster.

Battery life is ok and the power enough to keep a short beard trimmed without any problems, but it has problems with thicker and more hair, requiring you to rinse the trimmer to keep going with the thicker beard.

Overall, I like it. It is comfortable to hold during use, is 110-220v compatible, so you can take this with you when travelling without any worries.

column14: I purchased this full-size bottle after receiving a sample in my Birchbox and loving it. I've been using the liquid now for two weeks, and my skin is noticeably healthier. In fact, it's emboldened me to leave the house without any makeup on whatsoever. I'm 45 years old, and up until about 3 years ago, I looked maybe a decade younger than my age. Then I hit peri-menopause, and everything changed, including my skin. This is the first product that has give me back some of my confidence and has me thinking my skin and face actually look youthful! I have naturally oily skin, so I am only using the liquid, not the cream or the combo (my understanding is that for dry skin, the cream is recommended as well). It moisturizes all day. I use it on my neck, as well, and what a difference! I'm telling you- this is as close to a miracle product as I've found, and I was almost hesitant to write a review because I wanted to keep the secret to myself. But that wouldn't be nice. :) Definitely give this product a try!

column6: Adore Semi-permanent Hair Color
column13: Be careful with color selection for darker hair
column14:
I have naturally darkish red hair. I had previously used a temporary purple dye which had washed off to a light pink. I was just dying the underside of my hair, not bleaching first. I have no experience dying hair other than the very temporary dye which was my test to see if I could do this myself. Here are my thoughts:

Very pleasant smell
My hair felt really soft afterwards
The dye was a manageable consistency (not drippy or hard to spread)
The African Violet color was not at all what I expected, and I was extremely unhappy with the flat, ashy black I was left with.

Overall I think this is a great quality product, but that I bought the wrong color. On the lighter parts of my hair, I can see African Violet would have looked like a nice shade of blue had my hair been blonde or bleached. It just looks awful on darker hair. I would have given a five star rating had the color swatch been a better representation. I was looking for a vibrant bluish purple, and it was not that. In regular lighting at work, people thought I had dyed my hair black :/ I have since had my hair professionally bleached and dyed an awesome shade of purple, and will use Purple Rage to do a touch up when needed. If that goes poorly as well, I will modify my review.

* Update * I now routinely use Purple Rage and Hot Pink together to achieve what I was after. It looks as good as the professional job I had done. The colors blend well together and whichever you put on your hair first shows up the strongest, so it's easy to get cool effects like hot pink tips which fade into purple higher up. The colors fade fairly quickly, but using this stuff is so easy and leaves hair so nice and soft that I don't mind doing it monthly. The only thing is, while the Hot Pink fades to a nice, soft blonde on bleached hair, the Purple Rage really goes a dirty shade of greenish-grey. I just go over it with pink when I know I won't be touching it up for a while, that cuts the green out. Also, on my natural hair Hot Pink leaves a really nice, vibrant shine. Purple on my natural hair still just goes dark. African Violet on bleached hair still looks royal blue to me.green out. Also, on my natural hair Hot Pink leaves a really nice, vibrant shine. Purple on my natural hair still just goes dark. African Violet on bleached hair still looks royal blue to me.

column13: The toothbrush is great, but he apps need some work.
column14:
This toothbrush is great. I've tried using it with the app on IOS (iPhone, iPad), Android (tablet & phone). You need to use an app to change the settings which include timers (more than 1), speed/intensity, and order of functions. The charging base can be remove from the 4 slot toothbrush holder. The second button allows changing speeds without having to stop/start the session.
I don't always use the app when brushing, but the toothbrush remembers the last 20 sessions. It then synchronizes the next time the app is used while brushing.
The only bad thing is when sharing the brush with someone else or multiple devices with the app. The programmers did not consider this important. If multiple people use the brush, their brushing history is combined. If multiple devices are used during different sessions, the settings on the current device changes the settings for the next usage. If all the settings are not the same, chaos results.

column6: The Honest Company Honest Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30 2-pack 3.0oz
column13: Try other zinc based sunblocks with higher ZO concentrations
column14:
I try to be aware of and avoid "group think," but it seems this product's reviews here got to me. I bought a two-pack at Costco (before reading reviews) and was excited to be able to use this in the pool due to its non-toxic, all natural formulation. Zinc oxide is quite affective, but in the end I think what made this product "bad" is its lower concentration of about 9% Z.O. versus 20% of other "better" products out there like Tom's of Maine natural baby sunblock.

So the one week I tried using this product, I did not get burned, but I've never burned easily in my life. I'm still susceptible to sunburn but I can go longer in the sun than most people. I swam 30 minutes at a time with my dog and the stuff seemed to stay on my skin. The scent is decent. The consistency is thick, so you can't really rub it on like lotion. It really has to be coated on and it takes some effort to rub into your skin. It did not seem to come off in the water, and my skin was fine after. I also used this to do some yard work, but I was mostly covered up doing so (hat, long sleeves, gloves).

So in the end, if you want a natural alternative without oxybenzones and other potentially harmful chemicals, look for other varieties of Zinc Oxide sunblocks--the best zinc oxide sunblocks come in 20% or higher concentrations. Good luck!

column13: This sunscreen is the bomb dot com!
column14: We live in Texas where the sun beams down hotter than it does in Michigan, where we used to live. So a good sunscreen is a MUST HAVE. I'm a little sad that Banana Boat has stopped making their Ultra Defense MAX Sheer Protect in the lotion version. I've found it for sale, but people are charging just under $20.00 and up for the SPF 30 in the 8 oz. size. I use too much sunscreen everyday to pay such an exorbitant price. When I could find it locally, I was paying around the same price for the SPF 100 lotion that I paid for this product. My dermatologist told me that a good sunscreen is necessary when you use Retin-A that works to prevent aging like I do. I did my research thoroughly and it appears that the ingredients in this product are the exact same ingredients in their Ultra Defense. So I've been using Kids MAX for close to a month now and I can safely that this product is terrific, just like the Ultra Defense MAX. It really blocks out the sun well!

column6: American Crew Firm Hold Styling Gel Tube
column13: Big Improvement over My Old Gel
column14: I have not received the gel yet but I also bought this gel from somewhere else and have been very pleased with it.  I had been looking for a gel to replace the much less expensive gel I used for many, many years.  The former gel did the job but.....the flakes were out of control. I was never really sure, if the flakes were dandruff or the gel. As it turned out, the old gel caused most or all of the flakes.  I do not notice any flakes now. column6:
Sterling Silver Oxidized Celtic Knot Tree of Life Pendant Necklace, 18\" Jewelry 5 3 4 Y N Simple, beautiful This is a necklace I looked at several times on Amazon before deciding to get it.

I'm not big on jewelry. Bling is not my thing. I do, however, love Celtic knot work and similar designs.I work as a teacher in high school and prefer to have a professional appearance whenever possible which tends to include jewelry. This is a style I like because of how simple it is, but it still reflects my own tastes. Okay, down to the nitty-gritty:

Pros:
1. Simple, classic design goes with everyday clothes or professional style.
2. Brushed silver look works well with most/all skin types as well as most clothing colors.
3. Charm (?) is about the size of a quarter with the top branches just brushing beyond that diameter.
4. Not heavy, but thick enough to avoid getting bent easily.
5. The metal used will get a patina if you wear it a lot, but that will just give it that great weathered look.

Cons:
1. The chain is tiny. I know if you read the specifics, you will know this. The length makes it sit just a bit below the hollow of your throat.
2. The closure latch is TINY. I hate putting on necklaces because of the tiny ring that you have to open and hook and this one is particularly small for my nail-less (anxiety, thy name is education) fingers.

So, the only cons have to do with the chain which, to me, is not enough to lower the rating because it can easily be replaced. The charm (not even sure that's what you call it?) is the star of this piece and is amazing and beautiful. I added the chain information because if you have no desire to fuss with a small chain or latch, this might not be what you are looking for, though it means very little to me, personally.

I love, love, love the simple beauty of this necklace and will wear it often. column6: 925 Sterling Silver Cultured Pearl and Emerald Womens Trilogy Ring - Sizes 4 to 12 Available
column13: Beautiful Georgian or Colonial American style ring
column14:
I love love love this ring! I had been eyeing this ring for some time before I decided to purchase it, and I am very glad that I decided to buy it. The ring is delicate, the stones and pearl small, but the sizes given in the description will give you a clue that you are not getting big emeralds, as should the price. The setting is sterling silver, the style delicate, with scrolls and intricate design on the sides. It looks like something you'd see at any of the gift shops in Colonial Williamsburg or that you might see at an antique store or estate sale, if you are lucky enough to be able to find jewelry dating back to the 18th century (it is very rare and very expensive). I'm happy to own a reproduction. I have small, skinny fingers, so the small stones and pearl and the delicate setting suit me very well. It doesn't overwhelm me, nor make me look like a child who raided her mother's jewelry box. The emeralds are a lovely color--quintessential green with just a hint of blue, and are nicely complimented by the white metal and pearl. The emeralds are also set in so they don't protrude--nothing to get caught on clothing--they lie flush with the setting. The pearl too does not protrude so much that you will bang it if you wear it for everyday.

I love the scroll work in the setting--elaborate but not fussy and does not overpower the hand. It is the kind of ring that I can wear to work at the office, out to lunch with friends, out shopping as well as with a much dressier outfit to the opera or to a wedding.

I cannot recommend this seller highly enough, either. There was a slight issue with shipping, and when I contacted the seller via Amazon, the seller was happy to work with me around the shipping requirements. The ring arrived very quickly, in perfect condition. The next time I'm in the market for Georgian or colonial American design/style jewelry, I'll check out their items first. My co-workers thought I lucked out at an estate sale, an antique store, or a flea market, or that I had inherited it from a many times great-grandmother!

column13: Darker than the photo, but looks better over all than the photo as the light reflects off it.
column14: much darker than photo, but looks better over all than the photo as the light reflects very nicely highlighting the cut edges..  the hammering doesn't go directly down the middle of the ring, instead it moves closer from one edge toward the other as you turn it.  i like how the sides are smoothed and polished so it doesn't feel rough against your finger.  i took the other reviewers words into consideration and ordered a half size up from my actual ring size and it ended up fitting perfect, maybe a bit snug even, but feels nice.  at 20$ I'd highly recommend this ring for someone that wants a sturdy solid and thick looking ring that isn't dull or regular.

column6: Earring & Necklace Organizer - Acrylic Folding Jewelry Holder Screen - Holds 128 Pairs of Earrrings
column14: I'm very surprised by how many necklaces this can hold. I make my own jewelry so you can imagine how much storage I would need. One of the things I really like about this jewelry organizer is that either way you flip it, its the right side up. This makes it especially convenient for hanging longer necklaces as you can pull the chain down the backside and loop it over one of the bottom hooks.  I managed to fit 60 necklaces of varying sizes on this display and was still able to close it. I recommend putting thin chains on one panel and thick ones on the next and keep sticking to that pattern until the display is full in order to get it to fold up properly. I was allowed to review this at a discounted price in return for my honest opinion.

column13: Great necklace for someone who likes cats or just loves a pink sparkly treat.
column14:
My daughter instantly fell in love with this necklace! Here are our thoughts on it:

• Design and appearance: This is an adorable looking necklace. It’s cute, but not necessarily childish. The necklace is sparkly, which my daughter usually doesn’t like, but with this one she loved the way it looks. It could be a great gift for a cat lover, young girl or anyone who likes pink sparkly things.
• Quality: All the stones are set well and sparkly. There aren’t any major flaws I can identify. I’ll update that if we lose any stones or have any problems. The pink stone is a beautiful deeper rose pink, which she loved.
• Chain: The chain isn’t the heaviest or the most fragile. I can’t stand the super thin, fragile chains nor the thick masculine chains. This is the perfect mix between the two. There’s a short section at the end to adjust it.

We have no complaints about this. My daughter loves wearing it and gets a ton of compliments on it. I was sent this to test and review. That has no bearing on the rating or review I gave it, this is my honest opinion.

column6: High Polished Stainless Steel Versatile Unisex Money Clip
column13: Great moneyclip -- looks great and highly functional
column14:
I used to have a conventional money-clip based on the spring-effect of the curved metal. Unfortunately, it was made from cheap metal which would continually stretch beyond its elastic limits and would no longer work to hold smaller stacks of bills unless I bent it back into shape. When I saw this, the hinged latch seemed like a great idea to hold the bills in place, so I bought it. It's a great idea. It really works great with stacks of bills of various thickness. It also has a very attractive finish.

When I first got it I found it awkward to hold onto the clip with one hand and the bills with the other while trying to open the clip. Eventually I hit upon a technique of cradling the clip in my right hand while prying it open with my right thumbnail -- it works great and I can handle it very naturally now.

If you're new to money clips, here's a tip. A lot of people like to fold the bills in half before putting them in the money clip. The problem with that is, unless one is wanting to remove the bills on the outside, one has to unfold the stack which means finding the halfway point (that is, the surface of the bill on top) which can be awkward and tricky and even result in dropping bills. I prefer to fold the bills in thirds which means that the stack opens naturally when removed from the clip. Even more convenient is putting the clip in the middle of the unfolded stack and then folding it in thirds before putting it in one's pocket. It's a little messier that way -- loose coins in the same pocket can get caught between the bills (and typically drop out and roll away the minute the stack of bills is opened) but it makes accessing the bills very easy the minute they're out of one's pocket.

column6: MAZU Women's 2MM Tungsten Ring Classy Domed Comfort Fit Wedding Band Color Black
column14:
I got this ring because I have been looking for something like this at a decent price for quite some time. I did get it at a discount to review which is also a plus! I love it! I opened the package and couldn't wait to try it on. It is a thinner ring which I like. I got it to wear as my wedding ring because the ring I did have, the diamond fell out of and to me it just isn't worth or important to have a diamond ring. I like having something that is durable and doesn't cost a lot of money.

I also love that this is a hypoallergenic ring because I do have sensitivity to a lot of metals in jewelery. This definitely stays true to that, as I have had no issues with it hurting or causing a reaction at all. I have even gotten the ring wet and never had an issue with it.

It is a true black color as well, so no lie when they say it is black.

This is a ring I would be more than happy to pay full price for. It is durable, doesn't bother my sensitive skin and looks great. My husband loves it because it matches his ring (Of course I do too), and it was a great price. I also loved that the seller included a hand written note along with the ring and it had my name and ring size written discretely on the package to ensure I got the proper ring size! I love when people pay attention to detail and ensure that there are no problem.

column14:
Figures of eight encompass two clear crystals per pair. Each crystal is just under a 1/4" in diameter. There are twelve pairs on this 7 1/4" bracelet with a single one on each end of the clasp.

How easy is it to get on? This bracelet is a little tougher than some to get on but I can manage it by myself without assistance. The bracelet is presented in a quality gift box and once opened you will find the bracelet in a sealed plastic bag inside.

Mine came with a FREE, very pretty silk-like scarf (approximately 18" x 19") included in a separate box in the sealed package. The coloring of the scarf is mostly reds and greens on a white background - floral pattern.

PLEASE remember this is fashion jewelry. Although silver in color, it is not silver in metal but actually white gold plated alloy. I have to say that I don't like this bracelet as much as some of their others BUT that is my personal opinion. There is absolutely nothing wrong with this bracelet and if you like the look of it you can purchase with confidence! (Hence still awarding this bracelet 5 stars and not 4!) Product was received in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

column13: Very nice sparkly necklace; well constructed; nice box; good value for the money; see my photo
column14:
This is a very nice necklace for the money. It looks really good and seems well constructed. It also came in a good quality white box. The crystals look great and are quite sparkly. In the box was also a round mirror and a small microfiber cloth that can be used to keep the necklace shiny & clean.

There is some weight to this so it feels "substantial".

There are a lot of "circles" on this necklace so if you want something simpler than you may prefer something else... but otherwise you'll probably be quite happy with this and it would also make for a nice gift.

And the most important thing: no complaints from my picky wife (at least not yet!).

And you can't beat the complete refund if you're not satisfied.

NOTE: I was sent a free product sample for review. I was not paid or told what to write.

column6: Casoty Jewelry Star Trek Cufflinks Starfleet Command Cufflinks in Gift Box
column14:
These cufflinks are costume jewelry, but they have a very quality feel to them. The enameling on the emblem design is clear and distinct within the silver base (no bleeding of enamel over edges as so often the case in shoddy costume jewelry). The design is clean and sharp and looks like what it is supposed to look like. The posts are sturdy and solid without being too heavy or lightweight and function appropriately as cufflinks. The back piece swivels easily to allow for insertion and securing.

If you have someone in your life who is a Trek fan, these make an excellent gift. They arrive triple super well packed with each cufflink in a tiny zippered plastic bag and those two bags inside of a another similar but larger bag. The black gift box is in a sealed pouch which also has a zippered top and all of that is shipped in a padded mailer. If you want to give them as a gift and have the recipient view the mounted links, you'll need to take them out of their respective bags and put them in the included gift box. They are clean, sturdy, nicely designed, and you really couldn't ask for much more, especially at the current price.

Note: I was given this product in exchange for my assessment.

column14:
[[VIDEOID:ffe991ddababd25e20fe38fa73d5113a]]This review is for the "DUBAI EYE" World Premiere Rainbow-Colored Crystals Rose Gold Plated Ferris Wheel Women's Pendant Necklace Ladies Fashion Jewelry.

This necklace is simply stunning and I had no idea what the Dubai Eye was until I Googled it and realized that I now want to visit Dubai and go to Blackwater Island. (if you don't know what it is - you should DEFINETELY check it out!)

The pendant looks EXACTLY like the Dubai Eye and is gorgeous and pulls as many colors as the actual ferris wheel does in real life. The crystals are a TON of different colors. It looks like the designer put every color he could find into this piece!

The back is enameled BEAUTIFULLY and if you chose - you can flip the pendant around and wear it the other way! The enameling gives it a completely different look but still stays true to the Dubai Eye design.

The necklace is gorgeous and pairs with the pendant perfectly. You can take it on or off the chain. The chain is also a great length and the piece as a whole has a nice weight to it and feel. 5/5 stars for color pallet, design and uniqueness.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: TIGRADE 6mm Tungsten Metal Ring Polished Brushed Pipe Cut Comfort Fit Band
column14:
I'm a 5'10, 110 lb male who simply wanted to buy himself a fancy ring (I know it's a wedding band), and If that's along the lines of your situation, I suggest reading this review.

I bought this ring after doing a ton of research on jewelry. The different metals, the fake jewelry, and fake gems versus real gems and everything. It took me a very long time to settle on this ring (so many choices out there!)

I finally settled on Tungsten as a metal, an inexpensive and strong metal that's also quite flashy with a high polish.

It's day 2, I've purposely banged and scratched it against a few things (I mean it's cheap and I would like to know what I'm paying for), and each time I did so it held up fine. The polish stayed, the inlay didn't scratch (im thinking the whole ring is solid tungsten, which I highly recommend), and the band didn't change colors, react to my finger oils or soap from the shower, or turn my finger colors. It's quite heavy (as tungsten is) but its a great size for someone skinny like me. I got the ring in size 6.5 incase anyone needs to see a visual example of what the ring might look like on me. To be clear though, even 6.5 is too big for me (it only fits on my index finger), so if you have hands like mine and a similar height/weight, go with a size 6.

column13: A great looking pair of \statement\" earrings."
column14: These earrings are quite attractive and big (total approx. 2" long).  I usually wear a smaller earring, but thought these would be fun to wear as a statement earring, when I feel adventurous.  The earrings are a pretty crescent shape with a filigree swirl design of 18K gold plate over Sterling Silver.  The earrings are flat, sides are smooth, and they are lightweight.  There is a small Tiger-eye stone bead above two chains that hold up the crescent on each earring. The closing is the leverback which is much safer than the fishhook.  I have purchased earrings from the Amazon Curated Collection in the past and have been well pleased.  Looking forward to wearing these out to dinner soon.

column6: Isenretail Fashion 925 Silver Womens Double Zirconia Party Evening Earring 6MM 10MM
column14:
I don't really like to wear studs but sometimes dangly earrings just don't look right with an outfit.. I was excited when I came across these because they are kind of a hybrid between studs and dangles. My ear piercings are right in the middle of my lobe so these look very pretty on and you can't see the wire that holds the larger ball just below my earlobe. I've gotten a ton of compliments on them and people always ask me to see how they work which I think is kind of funny. One thing that is important to know is that the bottom portion which is actually the backing for the top stud part of the earrings fits very loosely onto the post. It comes with little clear plastic stoppers that go on the post after the backing to make them more secure but if you lost those then you wouldn't be able wear the earrings anymore because they wouldn't hold together on their own.

Note: I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

column14:
[[VIDEOID:4fe60896bea5ddeeeefc2770f0e9b35d]]This review is for the Stardust Magnet Clamp Dark Green Austrian Crystals Women's Bracelets.

This is such a fun bracelet! This bracelet is unique because you wrap it around your wrist twice, and then use the magnetic clasp to close it! It takes SECONDS to put on and holds very securely!

The sparkly diamond crystals are all contained in long mesh tubing that holds everything together and around your wrist. The mesh tube does NOT pull the fine hairs on my wrist or cause any type of discomfort. It is very smooth and soft against my skin. There are so many crystals that when the light hits the tubing - it is VERY glittery. I love this bracelet and it looked better in person then on the Amazon page.

The magnetic clasp is SO secure. And it takes seconds to put on. Wrap... and snap. So simply any age could operate this bracelet. In fact, that is what makes it really great for a younger person or even an older person whose eyesight is not the best. It is just so easy to put on anyone could do it.

5/5 stars for unique design, beautiful crystals and smooth mesh!

column14:
[[VIDEOID:8f3f7d8db2e37e0ca7249e3f31d67c51]]This review is for the 18K Gold Plated Black Enamel Women Vintage Jewelry Sets Austrian Crystals Statement Necklace Earring Set.

This is a classically beautiful set of enamel jewelry that would go great with a business outfit or even going out at night. It is fairly versatile. The black enamel makes it causal - but then the accent of crystal makes it flashy.

The piece has some good weight to it, it feels very quality. The pendant hangs nicely on the chain and stays center and flipped the correct way at all times. It can be removed from the chain and put on a different necklace or you can use the chain for something else.

The chain is simply beautiful and unique! It is made with gold beading work - not seed beads, but these are gold metal beads. It is SO pretty! It is very fluid and flows around my neckline perfectly. The clasp is secure and easy to operate. The necklace is a good length.

Last, the earrings pull together the look perfectly. They match the pendant and create a flash of sparkle near your face too. They are very comfortable and easy to take on and off. 5/5 stars for enameling, materials and design.

column14:
None were UV, as advertised (woulda been 3stars if 1/2 were UV).
Posts may not be the standard material for NEW piercings -- andbreak easily inside mouth (both of us who have tongue piercings).

Mostly 16ga (no 14ga horseshoes): that's minus 1 more star. 14ga=only ten 20mm (7/8") tongue & ten 16mm bellybutton (can also be used as eyebrow/etc).

16ga:
- 18 horseshoes - 16ga, 12mm diameter (If you really need eighteen 16ga, but zero 14ga, knock yourself out!! :-) )
- Labret (about 16 to 20): 8-11mm or maybe 12mm... some have thicker base-diameters than others.
- the rest = eyebrow (curves).

Good compatibility of colors with each other.

column6: QIANSE \Love in Paris\" Heart Shaped Corundum Copper Tennis Bracelet, Valentines Day Gifts"
column13: ~~ Dainty clusters of dark 'sapphire' and clear gems ~~
column14:
The pictures above do not do this bracelet justice. The sapphire colored cubic zirconia gems are WAY darker. This bracelet has a delicate look to it with each cluster having the dark blue center gem with a number of clear ones surrounding it. Each of the gems is "clawed" in, set similar to a ring. There are 22 clusters on this 6 7/8" length bracelet with an extra cluster and clasp enclosed for extra length if required. Each cluster is approximately 1/4" in diameter.

How easy is it to get on? This bracelet is a little tougher than some to get on but I can manage it by myself without assistance. The bracelet is presented in a quality gift box and once opened you will find the bracelet in a sealed plastic bag inside.

Mine came with a FREE, very pretty silk-like scarf (approximately 18" x 19") included in a separate box in the sealed package. The coloring of the scarf is mostly reds and greens on a white background - floral pattern.

PLEASE remember this is fashion jewelry. Although silver/white gold in color, it is actually only white gold plated alloy. If you are looking for something a little different, dainty but with some color then this could well be the bracelet for you! Product was received in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

column6: Vintage Midnight Black Sparkly Beaded Necklace Jewelry (Very Long - 37\)"
column14:
Quite honestly, I had hopes of finding a replacement for a black necklace I had lost. Since I was able to wear my other necklace with casual clothing as well as with more dressed-up outfits, I had second thoughts about keeping this new one because it is UBER dressy in appearance, and I didnt think I'd want to wear it with a more casual look. However, the more I "studied" it, the more attached I became to it ... and flat out stated that this necklace was NOT going back to the seller! And guess what!?! My sister called me the next day to say that she had found my "lost" necklace in her kitchen!

Although the following isn't anything near having to deduct a Star, you might be interested to know that the larger of the beads in this necklace are a LOT smaller than they appear in the picture shown in the ad ... although that doesn't bother me one tiny iota! When you see it in person you'll know exactly what I mean. In fact, you know how "sparkly" can sometimes tend to look inexpensive? Well, in this case, the sparkles are not the bright, blinding kind at all. Instead, they add a subtle, "twinkling elegance."

Bottom line is that I think you should get this necklace so that:
1. You can see it for yourself!
2. I can stop talking about it and WEAR it!! lol

The special message on the inner heart makes it a wonderful gift for someone you love. I gave this to my mom as one of her birthday gifts. She loves it and wears it often. Here are our thoughts on it.

• Versatile: It is really simple and elegant. You can wear it with anything, fancy or casual. It has nice quality clear stones around the heart that pick up natural like and make it sparkle nicely.
• Heart: The heart inside a heart design is cute. We both noted that the inner and outer hearts always stack together, like two puzzle pieces. We had both thought they would move around when wearing it so the inner heart would pop out and be perpendicular to the outer heart. Like one would be flat against the skin and the other would be sideways if that makes sense. This doesn’t detract from its simple beauty, just something we both thought would be a little neater.
• Chain: The chain is very feminine and on the thinner side. I have some other jewelry by the same seller that has chains that are a tiny bit larger that I personally prefer. I just like the more substantial, a little more durable chain, which my mom agrees about.
• Quality: This is where all of the jewelry from this seller really shines. I can tell they put a lot of time into coming up with unique, but not odd pieces that all have excellent quality. All of the pieces by them have little touches here and there, like the writing on the inner heart, that show they went above and beyond to make it a little more special. When I look at the jewelry up close I don’t see any obvious imperfections or anything off.
Overall, this has been a beautiful gift for my mom. I am marking down one star for the chain and that the hearts stay sandwiched together, I’d love to see the nice writing on the inner heart when she wears it. I was sent this to test and review.
